{"title_page": "NXIVM", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use American English|date= June 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Short description|American multi-level marketing company}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name = NXIVM Corporation\n|logo = NXIVM_Logo.png\n|logo_size = 100px\n|type = [[Privately held company]]\n|foundation = 1998\n|location = [[Albany, New York|Albany]], [[New York (state) |New York]]\n|key_people = [[Keith Raniere]] (co-founder, leader)<br />Nancy Salzman (co-founder, president)<br />[[Allison Mack]] (recruiter, leader)<br />[[Clare Bronfman]] (funder, leader)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/01/23/brooklyn-judge-finds-issues-with-nxivm-defense-fund/ |title=Brooklyn judge finds 'issues' with Nxivm defense fund |work=nypost.com |first=Emily |last=Saul |date=January 23, 2019 |accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|industry = [[Multi-level marketing]]; [[personal development]]\n|products = Personal-growth seminars\n|revenue =\n|operating_income =\n|net_income =\n|num_employees =\n|homepage = {{url|http://www.nxivm.com |NXIVM.com}} ([https://web.archive.org/web/20190412162926/http://www.nxivm.com/ Archived])\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''NXIVM''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|n|\u025b|k|s|i|\u0259|m}} {{respell|NEKS|ee|\u0259m}}) is a self-described American [[multi-level marketing]] company<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vox.com/2018/4/25/17275930/allison-mack-smallville-actress-sex-cult-nxivm-dos-prison-arrest-sex-trafficking-keith-raniere |title= Seagram's heiress arrested for role in controversial \"sex cult\" |first= Tara Isabella |last= Burton |date =April 25, 2018 |website= Vox}}</ref> based near [[Albany, New York]], who offers [[personal development|personal]] and [[professional development|professional]] development [[seminar]]s through its \"Executive Success Programs\". The company has been widely described as a [[cult]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/nxivm-keith-raniere-wellness-scam-sex-cult-848439/|title=How NXIVM Was the Ultimate Wellness Scam|last=Dickson|first=E. J.|last2=Dickson|first2=E. J.|date=2019-10-08|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref> and it was also alleged to have been a recruiting platform for a [[secret society]] (variously called \"DOS\" or \"The Vow\"), in which women were [[Human branding |branded]] and forced into [[sexual slavery]].\n\nIn early 2018, NXIVM's founder [[Keith Raniere]] and his associate, actress [[Allison Mack]], were arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on federal charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\">{{cite web |work= nbcnewyork.com |url= https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Leader-of-Secret-Upstate-New-York-Group-Charged-with-Sex-Trafficking-477966643.html |title= Leader of NY Group Branded Women, Made Them Sex Slaves: Feds |date= March 26, 2018 |publisher= NBCUniversal Media, LLC |accessdate= April 21, 2018}}</ref> Others associated with NXIVM were also charged with federal crimes. {{As of|2019|April|df=}} five people associated with NXIVM\u2014Mack, NXIVM co-founder Nancy Salzman, Lauren Salzman, [[Seagram]] heiress [[Clare Bronfman]], and bookkeeper Kathy Russell\u2014had pleaded guilty to various charges.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-47996207 |title= Nxivm: Seagram heiress Clare Bronfman pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |website= BBC News |author= |date= April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.thecut.com/2019/04/the-most-disturbing-details-from-the-nxivm-sex-cult-case.html |title= The Most Disturbing Details From the NXIVM Sex-Cult Case |website= The Cut |date= April 19, 2019 |last= Arnold |first= Amanda |accessdate= April 20, 2019}}</ref> Raniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019. On June 19, 2019, a Federal District Court in Brooklyn convicted Raniere of [[Sex trafficking in the United States |sex trafficking]] and [[racketeering]].<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/19/nyregion/nxivm-trial-verdict.html |title= Nxivm Trial: Leader Convicted After Trial Exposed Sex Cult's Sordid Inner Workings |last= Moynihan |first= Colin |date= June 19, 2019 |work= [[The New York Times]]|access-date= June 19, 2019 |issn= 0362-4331 | quote = On Wednesday, jurors in Federal District Court in Brooklyn sided with prosecutors. They found Keith Raniere, the leader of the cultlike group near Albany known as Nxivm, guilty of racketeering and sex trafficking, ending a six-week trial that exposed the sordid inner workings of the organization.}}\n</ref><ref>\n{{Cite news|url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2019/06/19/nxivm-cult-leader-keith-reniere-found-fuilty-sex-trafficking-case/|title= He told women he could help. Instead, he branded them with his initials and made them sex slaves.|first= Reis |last= Thebault |newspaper= [[The Washington Post]]|date= June 19, 2019}}\n</ref>\n\n==History==\nPrior to founding NXIVM, Raniere had created \"Consumers Buyline\", a business venture which was accused by the [[New York (state)|New York]] [[Attorney General of New York|Attorney General]] of having been a [[pyramid scheme]]; Raniere signed a consent order in 1996 in which he denied any wrongdoing, but agreed to pay a $40,000 fine and to be permanently banned from \"promoting, offering or granting participation in a chain distribution scheme\".<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120220\">{{cite web |title='Ample evidence' to justify investigation |date=February 20, 2012 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ample-evidence-to-justify-investigation-3337402.php}}</ref>\n\n===Founding and initial success===\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere and Nancy Salzman founded NXIVM, a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref> offering \"Executive Success Programs\" (ESPs) and a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\">{{cite news |url=http://www.newsweek.com/who-keith-raniere-self-help-guru-accused-sex-trafficking-and-branding-slave-863816 |title=Who is Keith Raniere? Self-help guru accused of sex trafficking |date=March 28, 2018 |work=[[Newsweek]] |accessdate=April 22, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"AECEB\">A&E Cults and Extreme Belief S1E1, aired May 28, 2018, last accessed May 30, 2018, https://www.aetv.com/shows/cults-and-extreme-belief/season-1/episode-1.</ref><ref name=\"NYT20180530\">{{cite web |title=The 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |date=May 30, 2018 |accessdate=May 30, 2018  |work=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html}}</ref> Raniere claimed that the programs' \"main emphasis is to have people experience more joy in their lives.\"<ref name=\"AECEB\"/>\n\nDuring NXIVM [[seminar]]s, students were expected to call Raniere and Salzman \"Vanguard\" and \"Prefect\", respectively.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120210\">{{cite web |last1=Odato |first=James |last2=Gish |first2=Jennifer |date=February 11, 2012 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secrets-of-NXIVM-2880885.php |title=Secrets of NXIVM |work=Albany Times Union |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Barcella |first=Laura |date=November 21, 2017 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/is-nxivm-a-cult-what-we-know-w512261 |title=Is NXIVM a Cult? What We Know |work=RollingStone.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"VF1\">{{cite web |last=Andrews |first=Suzanna |date=October 13, 2010 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |work=VanityFair.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' stated that Raniere \"adopted the title 'Vanguard' from a [[Vanguard (video game)|favorite arcade game]] ... in which the destruction of one's enemies increased one's own power.\"<ref name=\"THR201805\">{{cite web |title=Her Darkest Role: Actress Allison Mack's Descent From 'Smallville' to Sex Cult |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |date=May 16, 2018 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/how-smallvilles-allison-mack-went-actress-sex-cult-slaver-1112107}}</ref> Within the organization, the reasoning for the titles was that Raniere was the leader of a philosophical movement and Salzman was his first student.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\n===Cult allegations in early 2000s===\nNXIVM's training is a [[trade secret]], subject to [[non-disclosure agreements]], but reportedly uses a technique the organization calls \"rational inquiry\" to facilitate personal and professional development. In 2003, [[NXIVM Corp. v. The Ross Institute|NXIVM sued the Ross Institute]], alleging [[copyright infringement]] for publishing excerpts of content from its manual in three critical articles commissioned by cult investigator [[Rick Alan Ross]] and posted on his website.<ref name=Hochman>{{citation |title=A Forensic Psychiatrist Evaluates ESP |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/6047-a-forensic-psychiatrist-evaluates-esp.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin1>{{citation |title=A Critical Analysis of the Executive Success Programs Inc. |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5969-a-critical-analysis-of-the-executive-success-programs-inc.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin2>{{citation |title=Robert Jay Lifton's eight criteria of thought reform as applied to the Executive Success Programs |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5980-robert-jay-liftons-eight-criteria-of-thought-reform-as-applied-to-the-executive-success-programs.html}}</ref> Ross posted a [[psychiatrist]]'s assessment of NXIVM's \"secret\" manual on his website{{spaced ndash}}the report called the regimen \"expensive [[brainwashing]]\". The manual was obtained by Ross from former member Stephanie Franco, a co-[[defendant]] in the trial, who had signed a non-disclosure agreement not to divulge information from the manual to others. NXIVM filed suits in both New York and [[New Jersey]], but both were later dismissed.<ref name=\"Kohler\">{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=March 22, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201184159/http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |archive-date=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=NXIVM Corp. v. Ross |url=http://www.citmedialaw.org/threats/nxivm-corp-v-ross |work=legal case |publisher=Citizen media law company |accessdate=February 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2003, ''[[Forbes]]'' published an article on NXIVM and Raniere.<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\">{{cite news |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html |work=[[Forbes]] |location=New York |accessdate=April 24, 2018 |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref>  'I think it\u2019s a cult,' Edgar Bronfman told the magazine, going on to say that he was troubled about the 'emotional and financial' investment in NXIVM by his daughters, to whom he hadn\u2019t spoken in months.\"{{cn|date=March 2020}} In 2006, ''Forbes'' published an article about the Bronfman sisters, stating that they had taken out a [[line of credit]] to loan NXIVM [[United States dollar|US$]]2 million, repayable through personal training sessions and phone consultations with Salzman.<ref name=\"Forbes20060724\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2006/0724/044a.html |title=The Bronfmans And the Cult |last=Berman |first=Phyllis |date=June 24, 2006 |work=Forbes |accessdate=July 24, 2006 |last2=Gillies |first2=Andrew T. |last3=Novack |first3=Janet |last4=Egan |first4=Mary Ellen |last5=Blakeley |first5=Kiri}}</ref> Another ''Forbes'' article in 2010 discussed the failures of [[commodities]] and real estate deals by the Bronfmans made pursuant to Raniere's advice.<ref name=\"Forbes20100329\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/docket/2010/03/29/the-bronfmans-and-the-cult/#4da4f941538f |title=The Bronfmans and The 'Cult' |last=Vardi |first=Nathan |date=March 29, 2010 |work=Forbes |accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2006-2015===\nAfter actress [[Kristin Kreuk]] became involved with NXIVM in 2006, Salzman and her daughter Lauren went to [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]] to recruit Kreuk's ''[[Smallville]]'' co-star [[Allison Mack]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> The younger Salzman (herself a junior NXIVM leader)<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> bonded with Mack and the latter became involved,<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> although Kreuk would subsequently leave NXIVM.<ref name=\"TDB201803\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/smallville-actress-kristin-kreuk-horrified-and-disgusted-by-nxivm-cult-she-left |title='Smallville' Actress Kristin Kreuk 'Horrified and Disgusted' by Nxivm Cult She Left |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref> Mack became \"an enthusiastic proselytizer\" for NXIVM, persuading her parents to take courses, and, after wrapping production of ''Smallville'' in 2011, moved to [[Clifton Park, New York]] near NXIVM's home-base in [[Albany, New York|Albany]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Early 2007 saw a string of financial contributions from NXIVM participants to [[Hillary Clinton]]'s [[Hillary Clinton presidential campaign, 2008|first presidential campaign]], with over a dozen participants donating the maximum allowable figure of $2,300. The contributions totalled $29,900. NXIVM associates also gave $31,600 to the state Republican Senate Campaign Committee and provided $34,763 worth of air transportation, totaling $66,363.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2007/10/01/hillarys-30000-fans-are-her-cult-following/ |title=HILLARY'S $30,000 FANS ARE HER 'CULT' FOLLOWING |first=Charles |last=Hurt |date=October 1, 2007 |publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the Bronfman sisters allegedly pressured Stephen Herbits, a confidante of their father, to ask [[Albany County, New York|Albany County]] [[District Attorney]] David Soares, [[Governor of New York|New York Governor]] [[Eliot Spitzer]], and [[Attorney General of New Jersey|New Jersey Attorney General]] [[Anne Milgram]] to open criminal investigations into NXIVM's critics. NXIVM reportedly kept dossiers on Soares, Spitzer, political consultant [[Roger Stone]], [[United States Senator|U.S. Senator]] [[Chuck Schumer]], and Albany ''[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]'' publisher [[George Randolph Hearst III]] in a box in the basement of Nancy Salzman's home.<ref>[https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-13851003.php Witness: Bronfmans tried to apply political pressure]{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. Gavin, Robert. ''Times Union''. May 16, 2019.</ref> According to the ''Times Union'', NXIVM \"developed a reputation for aggressively pursuing critics and defectors who broke from its ranks, including using [[litigation]] to punish critics of Raniere, the organization, or its training methods.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/FBI-shifts-mountain-of-data-in-NXIVM-s-seized-13254160.php |title=FBI shifts mountain of data in NXIVM's seized computers |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 24, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\nThe World Ethical Foundations Consortium, an organization co-founded by Raniere and the Bronfman sisters, sponsored a visit to Albany by the [[14th Dalai Lama]] in 2009. The visit was initially cancelled due to negative press surrounding NXIVM,<ref>{{cite web |last=Ettkin |first=Brian |date=April 6, 2009 |url=http://www.newstimes.com/news/article/Dalai-Lama-cancels-his-visit-to-Albany-118447.php |title=Dalai Lama Cancels His Visit to Albany |work=[[The News-Times]] |accessdate=November 2, 2011}}</ref> but was rescheduled; the Dalai Lama spoke at Albany's [[Palace Theatre (Albany, New York)|Palace Theatre]] in May 2009.<ref>{{cite web |last=Caprood |first=Tom |date=May 7, 2009 |url=http://www.troyrecord.com/article/TR/20090507/NEWS/305079979 |title=Dalai Lama fills Palace with message of compassion |work=TroyRecord.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> \n\nNXIVM has been described as a pyramid scheme,<ref name=\"TimesUnion20171113\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Lawyer attacks NXIVM 'scheme' |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Lawyer-attacks-NXIVM-scheme-1032548.php |website=TimesUnion.com |publisher=The Hearst Corporation |accessdate=November 13, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Slate201803\">{{cite web |title=The Only (Alleged) Sex-Slave Cult Story You Need to Understand: Kirsten Gillibrand's Weakness as a 2020 Candidate |website=Slate.com |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2018/03/kirsten-gillibrand-alleged-sex-slavery-and-the-2020-primary.html}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT18Oct\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html?pagewanted=all |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |last=Meier |first=Barry |work=NY Times|access-date=October 18, 2017 |quote=In a letter, the agency said it would not look into Dr. Roberts because she was not acting as Ms. Edmondson\u2019s doctor when the branding is said to have happened.}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> a sex-trafficking operation,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-47563045 |title=Associate pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |date=March 13, 2019 |publisher=BBC}}</ref> a cult,<ref name=\"TheNation20141118\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thenation.com/article/190881/how-strange-secretive-cult-company-waging-legal-war-against-journalists |title=How a Strange, Secretive, Cult-like Company Is Waging Legal War Against Journalists |last=Cohan |first=William D. |date=November 18, 2014 |work=[[The Nation]] |access-date=May 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case - HoustonChronicle.com |date=April 19, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/members-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-federal-court/story?id=60645426 |title=Members of alleged sex cult NXIVM appear in federal court |first=A. B. C. |last=News |website=ABC News}}</ref> and a sex cult.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-44946059 |title=Heiress among four arrested in 'sex cult' |author= |date=July 25, 2018 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=January 14, 2019}}</ref> In a 2010 article in the ''Times Union'', former NXIVM coaches characterized students as \"prey\" for use by Raniere in satisfying his sexual or [[gambling]]-related proclivities.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20101122\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Ex-NXIVM trainer: Students are prey |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ex-NXIVM-trainer-Students-are-prey-824046.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=November 22, 2010}}</ref> Kristin Keeffe, a longtime partner of Raniere and mother of his child, left the group in 2014 and described Raniere as \"dangerous\", stating that \"[a]ll the worst things you know about NXIVM are true.\"<ref name=\"TimesUnion20140512\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=A split from NXIVM |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=May 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Media investigations of DOS===\nStarting with reports on the Frank Report blog in June 2017<ref>https://frankreport.com/2017/06/13/part-1-the-slave-women-of-dos-revealed/</ref> and bolstered by an October 2017 article in ''[[The New York Times]]'', details began to emerge about DOS, a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM, in which female members were allegedly referred to as \"slaves,\" [[human branding|branded]] with the initials of Raniere and Mack, subjected to [[corporal punishment]] from their \"masters\", and required to provide nude photos or other potentially damaging information about themselves as \"collateral\".<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher=ABC News |website=abcnews.go.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\">{{cite web |title=NXIVM: What We Know About Alleged Sex Trafficking, Forced Labor |author=Barcella, Laura |work=Rolling Stone |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=April 20, 2018 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/nxivm-what-we-know-about-alleged-sex-trafficking-forced-labor-w518483}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> Law enforcement representatives have alleged that members of DOS were forced into [[sexual slavery]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180327\">{{cite news |title=What is Nxivm? |date=March 27, 2018 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=http://www.newsweek.com/nxivm-keith-raniere-sex-trafficking-self-help-vow-dos-slaves-multi-level-861293}}</ref>\n\n[[Sarah Edmondson]], a [[Canada|Canadian]] actress who had been an ESP participant since 2005, said that she left NXIVM after Mack inducted her into DOS the preceding March at her home in Albany. Edmondson alleged that participants were [[blindfold]]ed naked, held down by Mack and three other women, and branded by NXIVM-affiliated doctor Danielle Roberts, using a [[cauterizing|cauterizing pen]].<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s5pRd-QTk_w |title=Canadian woman says she was ritually branded and indoctrinated by a 'cultish group' in the U.S. |last=CBC News |date=October 27, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news |title=Vancouver woman says scars from ritual 'branding' fuel her fight against 'cultish' group |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/sarah-edmondson-executive-success-programs-esp-nxivm-branding-1.4374048 |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] |date=October 27, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Appearing on an [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] television program about [[cult]]s, Edmondson would provide additional context on the use of the \"collateral\" concept, stating that it was used in innocuous forms from the earliest, outermost stages of NXIVM in order to acclimatize victims\u2014for example, collateralizing small amounts of money that one might forfeit if one did not go to the gym one day.<ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> The ''Times'' would later report that \"hundreds\" of members left NXIVM after Edmondson went public about her experience.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\nOn December 15, 2017, the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] newsmagazine ''[[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]'' aired an expos\u00e9 featuring interviews with many former NXIVM adherents, including Edmondson and [[Catherine Oxenberg]], who alleged that her daughter, India Oxenberg, was in danger due to the group. Several former members reported financial and [[sexual predation]] carried out by NXIVM leaders.<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QFV3zEFIs_k |title=Former NXIVM member describes being branded in secret sorority initiation: Part 1 |last=ABC News |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref> Edmondson was further featured in \"Escaping NXIVM\", during the first season of the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] [[podcast]] ''Uncover''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Escaping NXIVM |last= |first= |date=September 5, 2018 |website=cbc.ca |publisher=Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=November 13, 2018 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nSeven socially-prominent Mexicans, including Emilio Salinas Occelli (son of former president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]]) and Ana Cristina Fox (daughter of former president [[Vicente Fox]]), Rosa Laura Junco, Loreta Garza D\u00e1vila (a business leader from [[Nuevo Leon]]), Daniela Padilla, Camila Fern\u00e1ndez, and M\u00f3nica Dur\u00e1n, have been accused of involvement, according to an article in the ''[[New York Times]]'' published on May 26, 2019.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/sociedad/quienes-son-los-mexicanos-involucrados-con-la-secta-nxivm-3674611.html |title=\u00bfQui\u00e9nes son los mexicanos involucrados con la secta NXIVM? |newspaper=El Sol de Mexico |accessdate=May 26, 2019 |language=Spanish |date=May 26, 2019|trans-title=Who are the Mexicans involved with the NXIVM sect?}}</ref>\n\n===Criminal prosecutions and convictions===\nIn March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in Nxivm sex cult |last=Siemaszko |first=Corky |date=May 4, 2018 |work=[[NBC News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> He was arrested in [[Mexico]] and held in custody in New York after appearing in federal court in [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/leader-of-alleged-cult-that-ensnared-vancouver-woman-appears-in-court-1.4595940 |title=Leader of alleged cult that ensnared Vancouver woman appears in court |date=March 27, 2018 |work=CBC}}</ref> The indictment alleged that at least one woman was coerced into sex with Raniere, who forced DOS members to undergo the branding ritual alleged by Edmondson and others.<ref>{{cite news |title=Feds say self-help guru coerced followers into sex, had them branded with a cauterizing pen |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2018/03/27/feds-say-self-help-guru-coerced-followers-into-sex-had-them-branded-with-a-cauterizing-pen/?noredirect=on |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=March 27, 2018|last=Swenson|first=Kyle}}</ref><ref name=\"CBS20180327\">{{cite news |title=NXIVM female sex \"slaves\" allegedly branded with secretive group leader's initials |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/nxivm-leader-keith-raniere-charged-sex-trafficking |work=CBS |agency=Associated Press |date=March 27, 2018}}</ref> [[United States Attorney]] Richard Donoghue stated that Raniere \"created a secret society of women whom he had sex with and branded with his initials, coercing them with the threat of releasing their highly personal information and taking their assets.\"<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/>\n\nOn April 20, 2018, Mack was arrested and indicted on similar charges to Raniere's. According to [[prosecutor]]s, after she recruited women into first NXIVM and then DOS, Mack coerced them into engaging in sexual activity with Raniere and performing menial tasks, for which she was allegedly paid by Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Mack was further alleged to be second-in-command of NXIVM after Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/><ref name=\"TDB201803\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.justice.gov/usao-edny/pr/founder-nxivm-purported-self-help-organization-and-actor-indicted-sex-trafficking-and |title=Founder of \"NXIVM\", a Purported Self-Help Organization, and Actor Indicted for Sex Trafficking and Forced Labor Conspiracy |website=www.justice.gov |accessdate=April 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Smallville Actress Arrested for Role in Alleged Sex Cult that Branded and Enslaved Women |url=http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=April 20, 2018|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422083052/http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult/|archive-date=April 22, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/apr/22/smallville-actor-was-allegedly-a-top-member-of-cult-that-abused-women |title=Smallville's Allison Mack was allegedly a 'top member' of cult that abused women |first=Edward |last=Helmore |date=April 22, 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=April 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 24, Mack was released on $5 million bond pending trial and held under [[house arrest]] with her parents in [[California]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-actress-granted-bail-sex-cult-case-2018-04-24 |title=Allison Mack of \"Smallville\" granted bail in sex cult case |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gonzalez |first=Sandra |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/04/24/entertainment/allison-mack/index.html |title=Allison Mack granted bail in sex trafficking case |work=CNN |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=May 3, 2018}}</ref> If convicted of all charges, Mack and Raniere face a minimum of fifteen years and up to [[life imprisonment|life in prison]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult-keith-raniere/ |title=\"Smallville\" actress Allison Mack arrested for role in NXIVM sex cult |last=Park |first=Andrea |date=April 21, 2018 |work=[[CBS News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en}}</ref> On May 4, Raniere pleaded not guilty.<ref name=NBCMay4>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in sex cult |work=NBC News |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSalzman's home was raided shortly after Raniere's arrest,<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> and prosecutors stated during his arraignment that further arrests and a superseding indictment for Raniere and Mack should be expected.<ref name=TimesUnion20180504>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Keith-Raniere-Allison-Mack-head-to-court-in-12887478.php |title=Raniere, Mack appear in court on sex-slavery charges |work=Albany Times-Union |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref name=News10May4>{{cite web |url=http://www.news10.com/news/local-news/trial-date-set-for-keith-raniere-and-allison-mack/1159493630 |title=Trial date set for Keith Raniere and Allison Mack |work=Albany News 10 |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref> In late May, authorities moved to seize two NXIVM-owned properties near Albany.<ref>{{cite web |title=Foreclosure Complaint Reveals NXIVM Sex Cult Rituals In Upstate New York |date=May 24, 2018|access-date=May 29, 2018 |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2018/05/24/nxivm-sex-cult-foreclose-halfmoon}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, the ''[[New York Post]]'' reported that NXIVM had moved to [[Brooklyn, New York]] and was being led by Clare Bronfman.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2018/04/21/sex-cult-moves-to-brooklyn-and-is-ready-for-war/ |title='Sex cult' moves to Brooklyn \u2014 and is ready for 'war' |first=Laura |last=Italiano |date=April 21, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> On June 12, 2018, the ''Times Union'' reported that NXIVM had suspended its operations due to \"extraordinary circumstances facing the company\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-suspends-all-operations-12987928.php |title=NXIVM suspends all operations; founder's bail denied |first1=Steve |last1=Hughes |first2=The Associated |last2=Press |date=June 12, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Bronfman was arrested on July 24 and charged with [[racketeering]]. She was released to house arrest after signing a $100 million [[bail bond]]. Also arrested and charged with the same crime were NXIVM President Nancy Salzman; her daughter, Lauren Salzman; and another NXIVM employee, Kathy Russell.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4350140/clare-bronfman-seagrams-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult/ |title=Clare Bronfman, Seagram's heiress, arrested in Nxivm sex-trafficking case |website=globalnews.ca |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/nxivm-bronfman-sex-cult-racketeering-1.4759640 |title=Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM Bronfman and five others accused of racketeering related to operations of a cult-like pyramid group |last=Proctor |first=Jason |date=July 24, 2018 |website=CBC |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, 2019, Nancy Salzman pleaded guilty to a charge of racketeering criminal conspiracy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-crime-cult-idUSKCN1QU2Z2 |title=Self-help guru Raniere faces U.S. child porn charges; associate pleads guilty |last=Brendan |first=Pierson |date=March 13, 2019 |work=[[Reuters]]|access-date=March 14, 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/03/13/nxivm-co-founder-nancy-salzman-pleads-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Nxivm co-founder Nancy Salzman pleads guilty in sex cult case |last=Saul |first=Emily |date=March 13, 2019 |website=[[New York Post]] |language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=March 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-nxivm-case-smallville-actress-possible-plea-negotiations-keith-raniere-pleads-not-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Leader of alleged NXIVM sex cult pleads not guilty to child porn charges |website=www.cbsnews.com |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> Also in March 2019, Lauren Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering and racketeering conspiracy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Daughter-of-NXIVM-leader-pleads-guilty-13725939.php |title=Daughter of NXIVM leader pleads guilty |first1=Brendan J. |last1=Lyons |first2=Mike |last2=Goodwin |date=March 29, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> On April 8, 2019, Mack pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/apr/08/allison-mack-nxivm-pleads-guilty-racketeering-charges |title=Smallville star Allison Mack pleads guilty to racketeering in Nxivm case |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=April 8, 2019 |accessdate=April 21, 2019}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to charges of [[Illegal immigration to the United States|harboring an alien]] and [[identity fraud]]; bookkeeper Russell also pleaded guilty to [[visa fraud]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/nyregion/nxivm-clare-bronfman.html |title=Clare Bronfman Pleads Guilty in Nxivm 'Sex Cult' Case, Leaving Leader to Stand Trial Alone |last=Meier |first=Barry |date=April 19, 2019 |work=The New York Times |access-date=April 20, 2019 |last2=Moynihan |first2=Colin |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nRaniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706/|title=Video Center|website=NEWS10 ABC}}</ref> On June 19, 2019, he was convicted of racketeering and sex trafficking.<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\nIn January 2020, a federal lawsuit was filed in New York accusing Raniere and 14 associates of conducting illegal psychological experiments on members of the company and abusing them physically, emotionally and financially.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/29/us/nxivm-lawsuit-experiments-abuse/index.html|title=Nxivm leadership accused of illegal psychological experiments and systematic abuse in federal lawsuit|author1=Giulia McDonnell Nieto del Rio |author2=Madeline Holcombe |author3=Rob Frehse|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-21}}</ref>\n\n==Beliefs and practices==\n[[File:US v. Raniere GovtExhibit GX46.JPG|right|upright=0.7|thumb|NXIVM founder Keith Raniere]]\nIn NXIVM classes, rank was signified by the wearing of colored sashes, similar to belts used in various martial arts.<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/the-stripe-path-how-to-make-your-way-up-in-nxivm-1.4674369</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a 12-point \"Mission Statement\", which participants recited, pledging to \"purge\" themselves \"of all parasite and envy-based habits\", to enroll others in such courses, and to \"ethically control as much of the money, wealth and resources of the world as possible within my success plan\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/09/nyregion/nxivm-cult-trial.html |title=Former Sex Cult Official Describes Its 'Evil' Inner Workings |first=Colin |last=Moynihan |date=May 9, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Photographs of Raniere and Mack were displayed during classes, which would conclude with participants showing gratitude to the two leaders.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Uncover: Escaping NXIVM |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM conducted \"Intensives\" classes for 12 hours daily for 16 days. One cited price was $7,500.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/nxivm-trial-founder-keith-raniere-was-crime-boss-posing-as-guru-feds-say |title=NXIVM Trial Opens: Feds Say Founder Keith Raniere Was 'Crime Boss,' Not Guru |first=Pilar |last=Melendez |date=May 7, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Classes were divided into modules. In one module, \"Relationship Sourcing\", students were instructed to explore the benefits they would receive in the event of a partner's sudden death. Another module, \"Dracula and his ghouls\", reportedly discussed psychopaths and their followers. Other module titles included \"Best People; Perfect World\" and \"The Heroic Struggle\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/06/15/part-1-master-ranieres-secret-teachings-what-students-learn-in-esp-intensives/ |title=Part 1: Master Raniere's secret teachings: What students learn in ESP 'Intensives'! |date=June 15, 2017 |website=Frank Report - Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a practice, termed \"exploration of meaning\" that involved senior members questioning members as they delved into their childhood memories.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/nxivm-8-things-we-learned-from-sex-cult-expose-630616/ |title=Nxivm: 8 Things We Learned from 'Sex-Cult' Expos\u00e9 |first1=Elisabeth |last1=Garber-Paul |first2=Elisabeth |last2=Garber-Paul |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM taught that some people, called \"Suppressives\", try to impede progress within NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Witness-After-leaving-NXIVM-women-became-targets-13841142.php |title=Witness: Raniere bragged of wanting to 'break' follower Allison Mack |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=May 13, 2019 |website=Times Union |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> People who irrevocably turned against Raniere were said to have undergone \"The Fall\" and were labeled, in the words of a former member, as \"Luciferians, lost people for whom bad feels good, and good feels bad.\"<ref name=\"auto5\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/06/keith-raniere-nxivm-patents-luciferian |title=How NXIVM Used a Simple Tool to Build Its \"Sex Cult\" |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM members organized \"Vanguard Week\", an annual celebration of Raniere's birthday.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-turned-Lake-George-resort-into-annual-13836853.php |title=NXIVM turned Lake George resort into annual Raniere birthday jamboree - SFChronicle.com |date=May 10, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM has been associated with several related organizations. '''Jness''' was a society aimed at women, while the '''Society of Protectors''' was aimed primarily at men.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\"/> A third group was known by the acronym DOS for \"'''Dominus Obsequious Sororium'''\", a Latin phrase that reportedly translates to \"Master over Slave Women\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/feds-self-help-guru-kept-women-as-sex-slaves-branded-them-with-his-initials |title=Feds: 'Self-Help' Guru Kept Women as Sex 'Slaves,' Branded Them With His Initials |first=Tatyana |last=Bellamy-Walker |date=March 27, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref>  In 2006, Raniere founded '''Rainbow Cultural Garden''', an international chain of child-care organizations in which children were to be exposed to seven different languages.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/alejandro-sanzs-wifes-miami-school-closed-by-state-tied-to-nxivm-sex-cult-founder-10295903 |title=State Closes Midtown Miami School Tied to NXIVM \"Sex Cult\" Leader |first=Jerry |last=Iannelli |date=April 27, 2018 |website=Miami New Times}}</ref>\n\nSome members of NXIVM's inner circle were reportedly taught that, in past lives, they were high-ranking [[Nazi]]s.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Suzanna |last=Andrews |website=Vanities |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> Barbara Bouchey was reportedly the reincarnation of Holocaust architect [[Reinhard Heydrich]], while Nancy Salzmann was supposed to be the reincarnation of Hitler. Raniere reported he had been a leader of anti-Nazi partisans.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2018/04/08/adolf-hitler-herman-goering-nxivm-sex-cult-leader-raniere-told-followers-reincarnated-nazis/ |title=From Adolf Hitler to Herman Goering, NXIVM sex-cult leader Raniere told followers they were 'Reincarnated Nazis'! |date=April 9, 2018 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a complaint filed by a former NXIVM member, a medical doctor performed an experiment on her that involved recording her EEG responses while viewing footage of people being murdered.<ref name=\"auto5\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://assets.documentcloud.org/documents/4113542/Porter-Complaint.pdf|title=Porter Complaint}}</ref> Brandon P. Porter, the doctor, faced 24 professional conduct charges from the New York State Board of the [[Office of Professional Medical Conduct]], including \"moral unfitness to practice medicine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/article/NXIVM-doctor-facing-state-charges-12890993.php |title=NXIVM doctor facing state charges |first=Steve |last=Barnes |date=May 5, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://apps.health.ny.gov/pubdoh/professionals/doctors/conduct/factions/FileDownloadAction.action?finalActionId=12236&fileName=CHRG+253486.pdf&fileSeqNum=1 |title=Notice Of Hearing In The Matter Of Brandon Porter, MD |publisher=Office for Professional Medical Conduct, New York State Department of Health |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=July 22, 2019}}</ref>  In August 2019, Porter's license was revoked for his role in the experiments and for his failure to report an \"unusual disease outbreak\" which occurred at NXIVM's 2016 \"V-Week\" retreat.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-doctor-who-conducted-brain-studies-loses-14370824.php |title=NXIVM doctor who conducted brain studies loses license |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/08/22/dr-brandon-porter-loses-medical-license/ |title=Dr. Brandon Porter Loses Medical License |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n==Notable members and others==\nNXIVM was founded by '''Keith Raniere''' (born August 26, 1960).<ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\"/> In March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to [[NXIVM#Media investigations|DOS]] (a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM), including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\"/><ref name=\"news10.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706 |title=NXIVM TRIAL: Prosecution's opening statements lasted 90 minutes |date=May 7, 2019 |website=WTEN}}</ref> He was found guilty of all charges at trial.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chow |first1=Andrew |title=NXIVM Leader Keith Raniere Convicted on Sex Trafficking Charges. Here Are the Major Players in the Case |url=https://time.com/5568135/nxivm-allison-mack-raniere/ |website=Time |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=June 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere met '''Nancy Salzman''', a psychiatric nurse and trained practitioner of [[Hypnosis|hypnotism]] and [[Neuro-Linguistic Programming]]. The two founded \"Executive Success Programs\", a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\"/> offering a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>  In March 2019, Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/who-nancy-salzman-nxivm-co-founders-wrongdoings-shine-through-daughter-lauren-1431652 |title=Who is Nancy Salzman? Co-founder's daughter testifies in plea deal for NXIVM wrongdoings |first=Kelly Wynne On 5/21/19 at 11:22 AM |last=EDT |date=May 21, 2019 |website=Newsweek}}</ref> \n\n[[File:Bronfman sara.jpg|thumb|left|100px|Heiress Sara Bronfman, along with her sister Clare, bankrolled the NXIVM organization beginning in 2003.]]\n\n'''[[Sara Bronfman]]''' is the daughter of billionaire Seagrams chairman Edgar Bronfman Sr.  She was introduced to NXIVM by a family friend in 2002.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> She in turn introduced her sister, '''[[Clare Bronfman]]''' to NXIVM. Clare Bronfman was arrested by federal agents on July 24, 2018, in New York City and charged with money laundering and identity theft in connection with NXIVM activities. She pleaded not guilty in the [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of New York]] in Brooklyn. She was released on $100 million bond and placed on [[house arrest]] with [[electronic monitoring]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/crime-courts/feds-arrest-seagram-heiress-bronfman-nxivm-sex-slave-case-n894136 |title=Seagram heiress Bronfman pleads not guilty in NXIVM 'sex slave' case |work=NBC News| access-date=April 20, 2019 |date=July 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to conspiracy to conceal and harbor illegal aliens for financial gain and fraudulent use of identification. She faces 21 to 27 months in prison and has agreed to forfeit $6 million.<ref name=lyons>{{cite news |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=April 20, 2019 |newspaper=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Emiliano Salinas]]''' is a venture capitalist and businessman. He is the son of former Mexican president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]].  Salinas served as vice president of Prorsus Capital, a financial consortium with ties to Raniere and NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zimmerman |first1=Amy |title=Inside the NXIVM Sex Cult\u2019s Secret Plot to Take Over Mexico |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/inside-the-nxivm-sex-cults-secret-plot-to-take-over-mexico |website=The Daily Beast |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n[[File:Allison Mack at ComicCon 2009 NN.jpg|thumb|right|150px|American actress [[Allison Mack]] pleaded guilty to racketeering charges in April 2019 and is awaiting sentencing.]]\n\n'''Karen A. Unterreiner''' is a member who became Raniere's live-in partner beginning in the 1980s, and an early employee of his company Consumers' Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Raniere-stands-alone-13795442.php |title=Raniere stands alone |date=May 4, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> \n\n'''Pam Cafritz''' was the daughter of Washington-DC socialites Buffy and William Cafritz.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>  In the 1990s, she resided with Raniere and Karen Unterreiner in an Albany home.  Both Unterreiner and Cafritz signed consent agreements with prosecutors for their role in Consumer's Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/07/making-vanguard-proud-the-mays-men-bring-executive-success-to-arkansas/ |title=Making Vanguard Proud \u2013 The Mays Men Bring Executive Success To Arkansas |date=July 7, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref> Cafritz was a founder of JNESS, the Raniere-affiliated women's group.  Cafritz was reported to be Raniere's 'most important long-term girlfriend'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>  On November 7, 2016, Pam Cafritz died.  After her death, her credit card was charged for over $300,000.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Ordered-to-seduce-Raniere-woman-planned-escape-13968629.php |title=Ordered to seduce Raniere, woman planned escape from NXIVM |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Allison Mack]]''' is an American actress known for her role on the series ''[[Smallville]]''. Mack was reportedly recruited to the [[Vancouver]] chapter of NXIVM, along with her ''Smallville'' co-star [[Kristin Kreuk]].<ref>{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=November 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180502001435/http://www.macleans.ca/economy/business/how-to-lose-100-million/2/ |archive-date=May 2, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>  Mack was reportedly a founder of DOS, a Raniere-affiliated Master/Slave group. Mack was arrested on April 20, 2018, on charges of [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (criminal)|conspiracy]], and [[forced labor]] conspiracy.  Mack pleaded guilty to [[racketeering]] charges in April 2019, and was to be sentenced in September 2019. However, on July 15, 2019 the Senior U.S. District Judge Nicholas Garaufis postponed the sentencing until further notice to allow federal probation officials to conduct pre-sentencing investigations.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sentencing of NXIVM leader delayed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/amp/Sentencing-of-NXIVM-leader-delayed-14097454.php |newspaper=[[timesunion]]}}</ref>\n\n[[File:10.15.11NickiClyneByLuigiNovi2.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Canadian actress [[Nicki Clyne]]]]\n'''[[Nicki Clyne]]''' is a Canadian actress known for her role on the series ''[[Battlestar Galactica (2004 TV series)|Battlestar Galactica]]''.  According to reports, in 2006, Clyne became involved with NXIVM. In 2008, she reportedly requested to be let out of her contract to focus full-time on NXIVM.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/11/19/nicki-clyne-quit-acting-broke-her-contract-with-battlestar-galatica-producers-to-join-nxivm-mission-full-time/ |title=Nicki Clyne quit acting, broke her contract with Battlestar Galatica producers to join NXIVM mission full time |date=November 19, 2017 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n'''India Oxenberg''', daughter of actress [[Catherine Oxenberg]], was introduced to the group in 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/catherine-oxenberg-on-losing-her-daughter-to-the-sex-cult-nxivm-going-public-was-a-last-resort |title=Catherine Oxenberg Reveals How She Lost Her Daughter to the Sex Cult NXIVM |first=Amy |last=Zimmerman |date=August 8, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref> At Raniere's trial, a witness testified that India had spent a year on a 500-calorie-per-day diet.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/allison-mack-nxivm-trial-diet-500-calories-1443377 |title=Allison Mack reportedly forced NXIVM sex cult members to follow 500-calorie-a-day diets |first=Janice Williams On 6/11/19 at 10:42 AM |last=EDT |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Newsweek |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> In May 2017, India admitted to her mother that she was among those who had been branded.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-daughter-being-branded-nxivm/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg's Daughter Was 'Branded' with 'Cult' Leader's Initials: 'I Was Horrified' |website=PEOPLE.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> India left the group in June 2018, after Raniere's arrest.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-says-her-daughter-who-has-left-nxivm-is-moving-forward/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg Says Her Daughter Who Has Left Nxivm Is 'Moving Forward' |first1=Liz |last1=McNeil |first2=Johnny |last2=Dodd |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=August 7, 2018 |access-date=February 7, 2019}}</ref> In August 2018, Catherine Oxenberg's book ''Captive: A Mother's Crusade to Save Her Daughter from a Terrifying Cult'' was published.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.simonandschuster.com/books/Captive/Catherine-Oxenberg/9781982100650 |title=Captive |last1=Oxenberg |first1=Catherine |first2=Natasha |last2=Stoynoff |date=2018 |publisher=[[Gallery Publishing Group|Gallery Books]] |isbn=9781982100650}}</ref>\n\n===Critical former members===\n'''Toni Natalie''' met Raniere in 1991 when he was pitching his business \"Consumer's Buyline\".<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.democratandchronicle.com/story/news/politics/albany/2018/03/08/rochester-woman-battles-nxivm-keith-raniere/360847002/ |title=Rochester woman tells all about life with NXIVM's Keith Raniere, her ex |website=Rochester Democrat and Chronicle}}</ref> Natalie and her then-husband became top sellers for the organization.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>  Natalie recalled that she was able to stop smoking after a two-hour session with Raniere,<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> but this claim is disputed by her ex-husband.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/10/17/toni-natalies-keith-hypnotized-me-into-quitting-smoking-story-disputed-by-ex-husband-rusty/ |title=Toni Natalie's 'Keith Hypnotized Me Into Quitting Smoking' Story Disputed by Ex-Husband Rusty |last=Parlato |first=Frank |website=Frank Report |date=October 17, 2019}}</ref> Natalie and her son later moved to be near Raniere; her marriage ended shortly thereafter. Natalie and Raniere dated for the next eight years.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In the mid-90s, Raniere and Natalie operated a health-products store.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web |url=http://forbes/2003/1013/088 |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |website=Forbes}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 1999, Raniere's eight-year relationship with Natalie ended. Natalie would subsequently claim to have been the victim of harassment.<ref>[https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084744]{{dead link|date=June 2019}}</ref> In a January 2003 ruling, federal judge Robert Littlefield implied Raniere was using a legal suit to harass Natalie. Wrote Littlefield: \"This matter smacks of a jilted fellow's attempt at revenge or retaliation against his former girlfriend, with many attempts at tripping her up along the way\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.org/details/269747-natalie-jilted-boyfriend |title=Natalie Jilted Boyfriend |date=December 1, 2011 |publisher= |via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In 2011, Natalie filed documents in federal court alleging that she had been repeatedly raped by Raniere.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>\n\n'''Joseph J. O'Hara''' was an attorney who departed NXIVM in 2005 after accusing the group of misdeeds.   In 2007, O'Hara was indicted by Albany County.  It was later revealed that the District Attorney had allowed Raniere's girlfriend Kristin Keeffe to operate within its office as a sort of victims' advocate.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-pressed-district-attorney-3379748.php |title=NXIVM pressed district attorney |date=March 3, 2012}}</ref> Charges were ultimately dismissed.\n\n'''Barbara Bouchey''' was a client of Nancy Salzman, having been referred to her in 1988. Beginning in 2000, Bouchey dated Raniere. In 2009, Bouchey and eight other women (\"The NXIVM Nine\") confronted Raniere with concerns about abuse within the organization. That year, Bouchey left the group and later went to law enforcement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Guilty-plea-of-Salzman-ends-her-long-allegiance-13691433.php |title=Guilty plea ends Salzman's long allegiance to Raniere - TimesUnion.com |date=March 17, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Kristin Keeffe''' became Raniere's partner in the early 1990s.  In 2013, Keeffe gave birth to Raniere's son Gaelyn.<ref name=\"TU150920\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/tuplus-local/article/Legal-papers-NXIVM-officials-probed-finances-of-6516856.php |title=Legal papers: NXIVM officials probed finances of 6 federal judges, Senator Schumer, others |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 20, 2015 |website=Times Union}}</ref>  In February 2014, Keeffe broke with Raniere and his group. Fleeing the region with her son, an email bearing Keeffe's name explained: \"I have full sole legal custody of Gaelyn. Keith was experimenting on him. I had to get Gaelyn away\".<ref name=\"TU140511\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |title=A split from NXIVM |first=James M. |last=Odato |date=May 11, 2014 |website=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]}}</ref> Keeffe publicly described Raniere as \"dangerous\".<ref name=\"TU140511\"/>  In 2015, Keeffe alleged that NXIVM leaders had planned to lure critics to Mexico with an invitation to an anti-cult conference; once in Mexico, the critics were to be arrested on false charges by order of a judge who had been bribed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://culteducation.com/404-error-page.html |title=404 Error Page |website=culteducation.com|access-date=August 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811212201/https://www.culteducation.com/404-error-page.html|archive-date=August 11, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"cbc.ca\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084740 |title=TRANSCRIPT: Uncover: Escaping NXIVM - Season 1, EP 3 |work=[[CBC Radio]] |date=April 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TU151018\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Records-NXIVM-hacked-billionaire-s-emails-with-6576310.php |title=Records: NXIVM hacked billionaire's emails with Hillary Clinton, world leaders |work=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=October 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Sarah Edmondson]]''' is a Canadian actress. After leaving NXIVM in early 2017, she publicly denounced the organization, claiming that she was invited into \"DOS,\" a substructure within NXIVM operated by Keith Raniere and [[Allison Mack]], and was branded with Raniere's and Mack's initials at Mack's{{Contradict-inline|reason=Two sources used here are contradictory: the Hollywood Reporter article says it was Mack's home, but the New York Times expos\u00e9 says it was Lauren Salzman's home.|date=April 2, 2020}} Albany home.<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite web |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |accessdate=May 13, 2018 |agency=ABC News |date=December 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nxivm member was branded at Allison Mack's home |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nxivm-member-was-branded-at-allison-macks-home-video-1113006 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |agency=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> Edmondson showed the brand in a ''[[New York Times]]'' expos\u00e9 of NXIVM.<ref name=\"nyt\"/>\n\n'''Mark Vicente''', a filmmaker known for the 2004 film ''[[What the Bleep Do We Know!?]]'', began involvement with the group in 2005. Vicente testified against Raniere at his 2019 trial.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tonyortega.org/2019/05/09/filmmaker-breaks-down-describing-nxivms-duplicitous-ideas-and-evil-intent/ |title=Filmmaker breaks down describing Nxivm's duplicitous ideas and evil intent - The Underground Bunker |website=tonyortega.org |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Journalists and bloggers===\n'''James Odato''' is an investigative reporter who wrote for the Albany Times Union.  In 2012, Odato reported Raniere's history of pedophilia.   In October 2013, Odato was named in a lawsuit filed by NXIVM, along with Vanity Fair's Suzanna Andrews and blogger John J. Tighe;  all had written critically of the group.<ref name=\"politico.com\">{{Cite web |url=http://politi.co/1W2nbYE |title=Journalist on leave after tangle with secretive 'NXIVM' group |first=Joe |last=Pompeo |website=POLITICO Media}}</ref>  The suit alleged that NXIVM computers had been illegally accessed.   Shortly thereafter, Odato was described as being 'on leave' from the Times Union.<ref name=\"politico.com\"/>\n\nIn 2007, '''Frank Parlato''' was hired by NXIVM to help with publicity.  After concluding the members were being defrauded by Raniere, Parlato began blogging about the group on his sites \"ArtVoice\", \"The Niagara Falls Reporter\" and \"The Frank Report\".<ref>Vice News Tonight May 16, 2018\"</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\"/>\n\n'''John Tighe''' wrote about NXIVM on a blog.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secret-mission-A-child-589818.php |title=Secret mission: A child |first=JAMES M. ODATO Capitol |last=bureau |date=July 25, 2010 |website=Times Union}}</ref> In 2013, NXIVM accused Tighe of illegally accessing NXIVM servers using a former member's login information. Tighe's home was raided by the New York State Police, and his computer was seized.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-hacking-case-to-be-tossed-6827893.php |title=NXIVM hacking case to be tossed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=February 13, 2016 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Several months later, State Police announced the discovery of child pornography on Tighe's computer; he was arrested. Facing a possible prison term of 20 years, Tighe pleaded guilty to a single count in exchange for a five-year sentence in federal prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/06/25/is-john-tighe-innocent-heres-a-few-facts-to-consider/ |title=Is John Tighe Innocent? \u2013 Here're a Few Facts to Consider |first=Is John Tighe Innocent?-Here\u2019re a Few Facts to Consider |last=says |date=June 25, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\n==Films, documentaries and books==\n* [[Investigation Discovery]] will release a two-hour special ''The Lost Women of NXIVM''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/investigation-discovery-the-lost-women-of-nxivm-1202635465/ |title='The Lost Women Of Nxivm': Investigation Discovery Explores Sex Cult In Two-Hour Special |first1=Peter |last1=White |first2=Peter |last2=White |date=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[HBO]] has announced their plans of making a docuseries about NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/04/nxivm-documentary-series-hbo-jehane-noujaim-karim-amer-1202060308/ |title=NXIVM Documentary Series from 'The Square' Filmmakers Coming to HBO |first1=Steve |last1=Greene |first2=Steve |last2=Greene |date=April 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/hbo-plans-docuseries-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-1203073 |title=HBO Plans Docuseries on Alleged Sex Cult NXIVM |website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/tv/alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-focus-hbo-documentary-series-n996196 |title=Alleged sex cult NXIVM focus of HBO documentary series |website=NBC News}}</ref>\n* [[Catherine Oxenberg]] produced a film for [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] about her daughter's experiences with NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/tv/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime/ |title=Lifetime Is Making a NXIVM Sex Cult Movie After Founder Keith Raniere's Conviction |website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime-catherine-oxenberg-peter-facinelli-star-1202637998/ |title=NXIVM Sex Cult Movie Set At Lifetime With Catherine Oxenberg Producing; Peter Facinelli & Andrea Roth To Star |first1=Denise |last1=Petski |first2=Denise |last2=Petski |date=July 1, 2019}}</ref> It is titled ''[[Escaping the NXIVM Cult: A Mother's Fight to Save Her Daughter]]'' and aired on September 21, 2019. While Catherine Oxenberg served as the narrator and executive producer, the film starred [[Andrea Roth]] as Catherine Oxenberg, [[Peter Facinelli]] as Keith Raniere, and [[Sara Fletcher]] as Allison Mack.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lifetime's Trailer For 'Escaping The NXIVM Cult' Shows Seduction And Anguish |url=https://deadline.com/video/lifetimes-trailer-for-escaping-the-nxivm-cult-shows-seduction-and-anguish/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n* \"The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM\" is an upcoming book by Toni Natalie and Chet Hardin set for release on September 24, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/28/new-book-by-toni-natalie-the-program-inside-the-mind-of-keith-raniere-and-the-rise-and-fall-of-nxivm/ |title=New Book by Toni Natalie: 'The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=https://www.grandcentralpublishing.com/titles/toni-natalie/the-program/9781538701034/ |title=The Program |date=March 5, 2019 |via=www.grandcentralpublishing.com}}</ref>\n* ''Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life'' by [[Sarah Edmondson]] is a book set that was released on September 17, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/07/28/scarred-the-true-story-of-how-i-escaped-nxivm-the-cult-that-bound-my-life/ |title=New Book By Sarah Edmondson 'Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n* NXIVM was the subject on an episode ''[[E! True Hollywood Story]]'' which featured interviews from several journalists and the people that were once involved with the organization including Catherine Oxenberg, Sarah Edmondson, and actor and Oxenberg's real-life friend [[Callum Blue]].1\n*[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] released a podcast in 2018 on NXIVM as part of CBC [https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/uncover-season-1-escaping-nxivm-1.4675949 Uncover Season 1].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180421090811/http://www.keithraniere.com/ Website] of [[Keith Raniere]]\n* [http://www.scs.cmu.edu/~dst/NXIVM/ Three critical articles pertaining to the ''NXIVM v. Ross Institute'' lawsuit]\n* [http://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/ ''Times Union'' Special Report on NXIVM]\n\n{{Multi-level marketing}}\n\n[[Category:1998 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Albany County, New York]]\n[[Category:Colonie, New York]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1998]]\n[[Category:Large-group awareness training]]\n[[Category:Multi-level marketing companies]]\n[[Category:Privately held companies based in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Sexual misconduct allegations]]\n[[Category:Cults]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use American English|date= June 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Short description|American multi-level marketing company}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name = NXIVM Corporation\n|logo = NXIVM_Logo.png\n|logo_size = 100px\n|type = [[Privately held company]]\n|foundation = 1998\n|location = [[Albany, New York|Albany]], [[New York (state) |New York]]\n|key_people = [[Keith Raniere]] (co-founder, leader)<br />Nancy Salzman (co-founder, president)<br />[[Allison Mack]] (recruiter, leader)<br />[[Clare Bronfman]] (funder, leader)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/01/23/brooklyn-judge-finds-issues-with-nxivm-defense-fund/ |title=Brooklyn judge finds 'issues' with Nxivm defense fund |work=nypost.com |first=Emily |last=Saul |date=January 23, 2019 |accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|industry = [[Multi-level marketing]]; [[personal development]]\n|products = Personal-growth seminars\n|revenue =\n|operating_income =\n|net_income =\n|num_employees =\n|homepage = {{url|http://www.nxivm.com |NXIVM.com}} ([https://web.archive.org/web/20190412162926/http://www.nxivm.com/ Archived])\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''NXIVM''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|n|\u025b|k|s|i|\u0259|m}} {{respell|NEKS|ee|\u0259m}}) is a self-described American [[multi-level marketing]] company<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vox.com/2018/4/25/17275930/allison-mack-smallville-actress-sex-cult-nxivm-dos-prison-arrest-sex-trafficking-keith-raniere |title= Seagram's heiress arrested for role in controversial \"sex cult\" |first= Tara Isabella |last= Burton |date =April 25, 2018 |website= Vox}}</ref> based near [[Albany, New York]], who offers [[personal development|personal]] and [[professional development|professional]] development [[seminar]]s through its \"Executive Success Programs\". The company has been widely described as a [[cult]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/nxivm-keith-raniere-wellness-scam-sex-cult-848439/|title=How NXIVM Was the Ultimate Wellness Scam|last=Dickson|first=E. J.|last2=Dickson|first2=E. J.|date=2019-10-08|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref> and it was also alleged to have been a recruiting platform for a [[secret society]] (variously called \"DOS\" or \"The Vow\"), in which women were [[Human branding |branded]] and forced into [[sexual slavery]].\n\nIn early 2018, NXIVM's founder [[Keith Raniere]] and his associate, actress [[Allison Mack]], were arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on federal charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\">{{cite web |work= nbcnewyork.com |url= https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Leader-of-Secret-Upstate-New-York-Group-Charged-with-Sex-Trafficking-477966643.html |title= Leader of NY Group Branded Women, Made Them Sex Slaves: Feds |date= March 26, 2018 |publisher= NBCUniversal Media, LLC |accessdate= April 21, 2018}}</ref> Others associated with NXIVM were also charged with federal crimes. {{As of|2019|April|df=}} five people associated with NXIVM\u2014Mack, NXIVM co-founder Nancy Salzman, Lauren Salzman, [[Seagram]] heiress [[Clare Bronfman]], and bookkeeper Kathy Russell\u2014had pleaded guilty to various charges.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-47996207 |title= Nxivm: Seagram heiress Clare Bronfman pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |website= BBC News |author= |date= April 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.thecut.com/2019/04/the-most-disturbing-details-from-the-nxivm-sex-cult-case.html |title= The Most Disturbing Details From the NXIVM Sex-Cult Case |website= The Cut |date= April 19, 2019 |last= Arnold |first= Amanda |accessdate= April 20, 2019}}</ref> Raniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019. On June 19, 2019, a Federal District Court in Brooklyn convicted Raniere of [[Sex trafficking in the United States |sex trafficking]] and [[racketeering]].<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/19/nyregion/nxivm-trial-verdict.html |title= Nxivm Trial: Leader Convicted After Trial Exposed Sex Cult's Sordid Inner Workings |last= Moynihan |first= Colin |date= June 19, 2019 |work= [[The New York Times]]|access-date= June 19, 2019 |issn= 0362-4331 | quote = On Wednesday, jurors in Federal District Court in Brooklyn sided with prosecutors. They found Keith Raniere, the leader of the cultlike group near Albany known as Nxivm, guilty of racketeering and sex trafficking, ending a six-week trial that exposed the sordid inner workings of the organization.}}\n</ref><ref>\n{{Cite news|url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2019/06/19/nxivm-cult-leader-keith-reniere-found-fuilty-sex-trafficking-case/|title= He told women he could help. Instead, he branded them with his initials and made them sex slaves.|first= Reis |last= Thebault |newspaper= [[The Washington Post]]|date= June 19, 2019}}\n</ref>\n\n==History==\nPrior to founding NXIVM, Raniere had created \"Consumers Buyline\", a business venture which was accused by the [[New York (state)|New York]] [[Attorney General of New York|Attorney General]] of having been a [[pyramid scheme]]; Raniere signed a consent order in 1996 in which he denied any wrongdoing, but agreed to pay a $40,000 fine and to be permanently banned from \"promoting, offering or granting participation in a chain distribution scheme\".<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120220\">{{cite web |title='Ample evidence' to justify investigation |date=February 20, 2012 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ample-evidence-to-justify-investigation-3337402.php}}</ref>\n\n===Founding and initial success===\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere and Nancy Salzman founded NXIVM, a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref> offering \"Executive Success Programs\" (ESPs) and a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\">{{cite news |url=http://www.newsweek.com/who-keith-raniere-self-help-guru-accused-sex-trafficking-and-branding-slave-863816 |title=Who is Keith Raniere? Self-help guru accused of sex trafficking |date=March 28, 2018 |work=[[Newsweek]] |accessdate=April 22, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"AECEB\">A&E Cults and Extreme Belief S1E1, aired May 28, 2018, last accessed May 30, 2018, https://www.aetv.com/shows/cults-and-extreme-belief/season-1/episode-1.</ref><ref name=\"NYT20180530\">{{cite web |title=The 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |date=May 30, 2018 |accessdate=May 30, 2018  |work=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html}}</ref> Raniere claimed that the programs' \"main emphasis is to have people experience more joy in their lives.\"<ref name=\"AECEB\"/>\n\nDuring NXIVM [[seminar]]s, students were expected to call Raniere and Salzman \"Vanguard\" and \"Prefect\", respectively.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20120210\">{{cite web |last1=Odato |first=James |last2=Gish |first2=Jennifer |date=February 11, 2012 |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secrets-of-NXIVM-2880885.php |title=Secrets of NXIVM |work=Albany Times Union |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Barcella |first=Laura |date=November 21, 2017 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/is-nxivm-a-cult-what-we-know-w512261 |title=Is NXIVM a Cult? What We Know |work=RollingStone.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"VF1\">{{cite web |last=Andrews |first=Suzanna |date=October 13, 2010 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |work=VanityFair.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' stated that Raniere \"adopted the title 'Vanguard' from a [[Vanguard (video game)|favorite arcade game]] ... in which the destruction of one's enemies increased one's own power.\"<ref name=\"THR201805\">{{cite web |title=Her Darkest Role: Actress Allison Mack's Descent From 'Smallville' to Sex Cult |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |date=May 16, 2018 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/how-smallvilles-allison-mack-went-actress-sex-cult-slaver-1112107}}</ref> Within the organization, the reasoning for the titles was that Raniere was the leader of a philosophical movement and Salzman was his first student.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\n===Cult allegations in early 2000s===\nNXIVM's training is a [[trade secret]], subject to [[non-disclosure agreements]], but reportedly uses a technique the organization calls \"rational inquiry\" to facilitate personal and professional development. In 2003, [[NXIVM Corp. v. The Ross Institute|NXIVM sued the Ross Institute]], alleging [[copyright infringement]] for publishing excerpts of content from its manual in three critical articles commissioned by cult investigator [[Rick Alan Ross]] and posted on his website.<ref name=Hochman>{{citation |title=A Forensic Psychiatrist Evaluates ESP |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/6047-a-forensic-psychiatrist-evaluates-esp.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin1>{{citation |title=A Critical Analysis of the Executive Success Programs Inc. |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5969-a-critical-analysis-of-the-executive-success-programs-inc.html}}</ref><ref name=Martin2>{{citation |title=Robert Jay Lifton's eight criteria of thought reform as applied to the Executive Success Programs |date=February 2003 |publisher=Cult Education Institute |url=https://culteducation.com/group/907-nxivm/5980-robert-jay-liftons-eight-criteria-of-thought-reform-as-applied-to-the-executive-success-programs.html}}</ref> Ross posted a [[psychiatrist]]'s assessment of NXIVM's \"secret\" manual on his website{{spaced ndash}}the report called the regimen \"expensive [[brainwashing]]\". The manual was obtained by Ross from former member Stephanie Franco, a co-[[defendant]] in the trial, who had signed a non-disclosure agreement not to divulge information from the manual to others. NXIVM filed suits in both New York and [[New Jersey]], but both were later dismissed.<ref name=\"Kohler\">{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=March 22, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201184159/http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |archive-date=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=NXIVM Corp. v. Ross |url=http://www.citmedialaw.org/threats/nxivm-corp-v-ross |work=legal case |publisher=Citizen media law company |accessdate=February 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2003, ''[[Forbes]]'' published an article on NXIVM and Raniere.<ref name=\"Forbes20031013\">{{cite news |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2003/1013/088.html |work=[[Forbes]] |location=New York |accessdate=April 24, 2018 |date=October 13, 2003}}</ref>  'I think it\u2019s a cult,' Edgar Bronfman told the magazine, going on to say that he was troubled about the 'emotional and financial' investment in NXIVM by his daughters, to whom he hadn\u2019t spoken in months.\"{{cn|date=March 2020}} In 2006, ''Forbes'' published an article about the Bronfman sisters, stating that they had taken out a [[line of credit]] to loan NXIVM [[United States dollar|US$]]2 million, repayable through personal training sessions and phone consultations with Salzman.<ref name=\"Forbes20060724\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2006/0724/044a.html |title=The Bronfmans And the Cult |last=Berman |first=Phyllis |date=June 24, 2006 |work=Forbes |accessdate=July 24, 2006 |last2=Gillies |first2=Andrew T. |last3=Novack |first3=Janet |last4=Egan |first4=Mary Ellen |last5=Blakeley |first5=Kiri}}</ref> Another ''Forbes'' article in 2010 discussed the failures of [[commodities]] and real estate deals by the Bronfmans made pursuant to Raniere's advice.<ref name=\"Forbes20100329\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/docket/2010/03/29/the-bronfmans-and-the-cult/#4da4f941538f |title=The Bronfmans and The 'Cult' |last=Vardi |first=Nathan |date=March 29, 2010 |work=Forbes |accessdate=February 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2006-2015===\nAfter actress [[Kristin Kreuk]] became involved with NXIVM in 2006, Salzman and her daughter Lauren went to [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]] to recruit Kreuk's ''[[Smallville]]'' co-star [[Allison Mack]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> The younger Salzman (herself a junior NXIVM leader)<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> bonded with Mack and the latter became involved,<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> although Kreuk would subsequently leave NXIVM.<ref name=\"TDB201803\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/smallville-actress-kristin-kreuk-horrified-and-disgusted-by-nxivm-cult-she-left |title='Smallville' Actress Kristin Kreuk 'Horrified and Disgusted' by Nxivm Cult She Left |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref> Mack became \"an enthusiastic proselytizer\" for NXIVM, persuading her parents to take courses, and, after wrapping production of ''Smallville'' in 2011, moved to [[Clifton Park, New York]] near NXIVM's home-base in [[Albany, New York|Albany]].<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Early 2007 saw a string of financial contributions from NXIVM participants to [[Hillary Clinton]]'s [[Hillary Clinton presidential campaign, 2008|first presidential campaign]], with over a dozen participants donating the maximum allowable figure of $2,300. The contributions totalled $29,900. NXIVM associates also gave $31,600 to the state Republican Senate Campaign Committee and provided $34,763 worth of air transportation, totaling $66,363.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2007/10/01/hillarys-30000-fans-are-her-cult-following/ |title=HILLARY'S $30,000 FANS ARE HER 'CULT' FOLLOWING |first=Charles |last=Hurt |date=October 1, 2007 |publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the Bronfman sisters allegedly pressured Stephen Herbits, a confidante of their father, to ask [[Albany County, New York|Albany County]] [[District Attorney]] David Soares, [[Governor of New York|New York Governor]] [[Eliot Spitzer]], and [[Attorney General of New Jersey|New Jersey Attorney General]] [[Anne Milgram]] to open criminal investigations into NXIVM's critics. NXIVM reportedly kept dossiers on Soares, Spitzer, political consultant [[Roger Stone]], [[United States Senator|U.S. Senator]] [[Chuck Schumer]], and Albany ''[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]'' publisher [[George Randolph Hearst III]] in a box in the basement of Nancy Salzman's home.<ref>[https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-13851003.php Witness: Bronfmans tried to apply political pressure]{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. Gavin, Robert. ''Times Union''. May 16, 2019.</ref> According to the ''Times Union'', NXIVM \"developed a reputation for aggressively pursuing critics and defectors who broke from its ranks, including using [[litigation]] to punish critics of Raniere, the organization, or its training methods.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/FBI-shifts-mountain-of-data-in-NXIVM-s-seized-13254160.php |title=FBI shifts mountain of data in NXIVM's seized computers |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 24, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\nThe World Ethical Foundations Consortium, an organization co-founded by Raniere and the Bronfman sisters, sponsored a visit to Albany by the [[14th Dalai Lama]] in 2009. The visit was initially cancelled due to negative press surrounding NXIVM,<ref>{{cite web |last=Ettkin |first=Brian |date=April 6, 2009 |url=http://www.newstimes.com/news/article/Dalai-Lama-cancels-his-visit-to-Albany-118447.php |title=Dalai Lama Cancels His Visit to Albany |work=[[The News-Times]] |accessdate=November 2, 2011}}</ref> but was rescheduled; the Dalai Lama spoke at Albany's [[Palace Theatre (Albany, New York)|Palace Theatre]] in May 2009.<ref>{{cite web |last=Caprood |first=Tom |date=May 7, 2009 |url=http://www.troyrecord.com/article/TR/20090507/NEWS/305079979 |title=Dalai Lama fills Palace with message of compassion |work=TroyRecord.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref> \n\nNXIVM has been described as a pyramid scheme,<ref name=\"TimesUnion20171113\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Lawyer attacks NXIVM 'scheme' |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Lawyer-attacks-NXIVM-scheme-1032548.php |website=TimesUnion.com |publisher=The Hearst Corporation |accessdate=November 13, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Slate201803\">{{cite web |title=The Only (Alleged) Sex-Slave Cult Story You Need to Understand: Kirsten Gillibrand's Weakness as a 2020 Candidate |website=Slate.com |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2018/03/kirsten-gillibrand-alleged-sex-slavery-and-the-2020-primary.html}}</ref><ref name=\"NYT18Oct\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html?pagewanted=all |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |last=Meier |first=Barry |work=NY Times|access-date=October 18, 2017 |quote=In a letter, the agency said it would not look into Dr. Roberts because she was not acting as Ms. Edmondson\u2019s doctor when the branding is said to have happened.}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> a sex-trafficking operation,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-47563045 |title=Associate pleads guilty in 'sex cult' case |date=March 13, 2019 |publisher=BBC}}</ref> a cult,<ref name=\"TheNation20141118\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thenation.com/article/190881/how-strange-secretive-cult-company-waging-legal-war-against-journalists |title=How a Strange, Secretive, Cult-like Company Is Waging Legal War Against Journalists |last=Cohan |first=William D. |date=November 18, 2014 |work=[[The Nation]] |access-date=May 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case - HoustonChronicle.com |date=April 19, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/members-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-federal-court/story?id=60645426 |title=Members of alleged sex cult NXIVM appear in federal court |first=A. B. C. |last=News |website=ABC News}}</ref> and a sex cult.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-44946059 |title=Heiress among four arrested in 'sex cult' |author= |date=July 25, 2018 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=January 14, 2019}}</ref> In a 2010 article in the ''Times Union'', former NXIVM coaches characterized students as \"prey\" for use by Raniere in satisfying his sexual or [[gambling]]-related proclivities.<ref name=\"TimesUnion20101122\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=Ex-NXIVM trainer: Students are prey |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Ex-NXIVM-trainer-Students-are-prey-824046.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=November 22, 2010}}</ref> Kristin Keeffe, a longtime partner of Raniere and mother of his child, left the group in 2014 and described Raniere as \"dangerous\", stating that \"[a]ll the worst things you know about NXIVM are true.\"<ref name=\"TimesUnion20140512\">{{cite web |last=Odato |first=James |title=A split from NXIVM |url=http://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |newspaper=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |date=May 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Media investigations of DOS===\nStarting with reports on the Frank Report blog in June 2017<ref>https://frankreport.com/2017/06/13/part-1-the-slave-women-of-dos-revealed/</ref> and bolstered by an October 2017 article in ''[[The New York Times]]'', details began to emerge about DOS, a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM, in which female members were allegedly referred to as \"slaves,\" [[human branding|branded]] with the initials of Raniere and Mack, subjected to [[corporal punishment]] from their \"masters\", and required to provide nude photos or other potentially damaging information about themselves as \"collateral\".<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher=ABC News |website=abcnews.go.com |accessdate=February 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\">{{cite web |title=NXIVM: What We Know About Alleged Sex Trafficking, Forced Labor |author=Barcella, Laura |work=Rolling Stone |date=March 28, 2018 |accessdate=April 20, 2018 |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/nxivm-what-we-know-about-alleged-sex-trafficking-forced-labor-w518483}}</ref><ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> Law enforcement representatives have alleged that members of DOS were forced into [[sexual slavery]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180327\">{{cite news |title=What is Nxivm? |date=March 27, 2018 |accessdate=April 18, 2018 |url=http://www.newsweek.com/nxivm-keith-raniere-sex-trafficking-self-help-vow-dos-slaves-multi-level-861293}}</ref>\n\n[[Sarah Edmondson]], a [[Canada|Canadian]] actress who had been an ESP participant since 2005, said that she left NXIVM after Mack inducted her into DOS the preceding March at her home in Albany. Edmondson alleged that participants were [[blindfold]]ed naked, held down by Mack and three other women, and branded by NXIVM-affiliated doctor Danielle Roberts, using a [[cauterizing|cauterizing pen]].<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s5pRd-QTk_w |title=Canadian woman says she was ritually branded and indoctrinated by a 'cultish group' in the U.S. |last=CBC News |date=October 27, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news |title=Vancouver woman says scars from ritual 'branding' fuel her fight against 'cultish' group |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/sarah-edmondson-executive-success-programs-esp-nxivm-branding-1.4374048 |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] |date=October 27, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Appearing on an [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] television program about [[cult]]s, Edmondson would provide additional context on the use of the \"collateral\" concept, stating that it was used in innocuous forms from the earliest, outermost stages of NXIVM in order to acclimatize victims\u2014for example, collateralizing small amounts of money that one might forfeit if one did not go to the gym one day.<ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/> The ''Times'' would later report that \"hundreds\" of members left NXIVM after Edmondson went public about her experience.<ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>\n\nOn December 15, 2017, the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] newsmagazine ''[[20/20 (U.S. TV series)|20/20]]'' aired an expos\u00e9 featuring interviews with many former NXIVM adherents, including Edmondson and [[Catherine Oxenberg]], who alleged that her daughter, India Oxenberg, was in danger due to the group. Several former members reported financial and [[sexual predation]] carried out by NXIVM leaders.<ref name=\"NYT18Oct\"/><ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QFV3zEFIs_k |title=Former NXIVM member describes being branded in secret sorority initiation: Part 1 |last=ABC News |date=December 16, 2017 |publisher= |via=YouTube}}</ref> Edmondson was further featured in \"Escaping NXIVM\", during the first season of the [[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] [[podcast]] ''Uncover''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Escaping NXIVM |last= |first= |date=September 5, 2018 |website=cbc.ca |publisher=Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=November 13, 2018 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nSeven socially-prominent Mexicans, including Emilio Salinas Occelli (son of former president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]]) and Ana Cristina Fox (daughter of former president [[Vicente Fox]]), Rosa Laura Junco, Loreta Garza D\u00e1vila (a business leader from [[Nuevo Leon]]), Daniela Padilla, Camila Fern\u00e1ndez, and M\u00f3nica Dur\u00e1n, have been accused of involvement, according to an article in the ''[[New York Times]]'' published on May 26, 2019.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/sociedad/quienes-son-los-mexicanos-involucrados-con-la-secta-nxivm-3674611.html |title=\u00bfQui\u00e9nes son los mexicanos involucrados con la secta NXIVM? |newspaper=El Sol de Mexico |accessdate=May 26, 2019 |language=Spanish |date=May 26, 2019|trans-title=Who are the Mexicans involved with the NXIVM sect?}}</ref>\n\n===Criminal prosecutions and convictions===\nIn March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to DOS, including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in Nxivm sex cult |last=Siemaszko |first=Corky |date=May 4, 2018 |work=[[NBC News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> He was arrested in [[Mexico]] and held in custody in New York after appearing in federal court in [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/leader-of-alleged-cult-that-ensnared-vancouver-woman-appears-in-court-1.4595940 |title=Leader of alleged cult that ensnared Vancouver woman appears in court |date=March 27, 2018 |work=CBC}}</ref> The indictment alleged that at least one woman was coerced into sex with Raniere, who forced DOS members to undergo the branding ritual alleged by Edmondson and others.<ref>{{cite news |title=Feds say self-help guru coerced followers into sex, had them branded with a cauterizing pen |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2018/03/27/feds-say-self-help-guru-coerced-followers-into-sex-had-them-branded-with-a-cauterizing-pen/?noredirect=on |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=March 27, 2018|last=Swenson|first=Kyle}}</ref><ref name=\"CBS20180327\">{{cite news |title=NXIVM female sex \"slaves\" allegedly branded with secretive group leader's initials |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/nxivm-leader-keith-raniere-charged-sex-trafficking |work=CBS |agency=Associated Press |date=March 27, 2018}}</ref> [[United States Attorney]] Richard Donoghue stated that Raniere \"created a secret society of women whom he had sex with and branded with his initials, coercing them with the threat of releasing their highly personal information and taking their assets.\"<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/>\n\nOn April 20, 2018, Mack was arrested and indicted on similar charges to Raniere's. According to [[prosecutor]]s, after she recruited women into first NXIVM and then DOS, Mack coerced them into engaging in sexual activity with Raniere and performing menial tasks, for which she was allegedly paid by Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/> Mack was further alleged to be second-in-command of NXIVM after Raniere.<ref name=\"THR201805\"/><ref name=\"TDB201803\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.justice.gov/usao-edny/pr/founder-nxivm-purported-self-help-organization-and-actor-indicted-sex-trafficking-and |title=Founder of \"NXIVM\", a Purported Self-Help Organization, and Actor Indicted for Sex Trafficking and Forced Labor Conspiracy |website=www.justice.gov |accessdate=April 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Smallville Actress Arrested for Role in Alleged Sex Cult that Branded and Enslaved Women |url=http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=April 20, 2018|access-date=April 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422083052/http://time.com/5248810/allison-mack-keith-raniere-nxivm-sex-cult/|archive-date=April 22, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/apr/22/smallville-actor-was-allegedly-a-top-member-of-cult-that-abused-women |title=Smallville's Allison Mack was allegedly a 'top member' of cult that abused women |first=Edward |last=Helmore |date=April 22, 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=April 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 24, Mack was released on $5 million bond pending trial and held under [[house arrest]] with her parents in [[California]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-actress-granted-bail-sex-cult-case-2018-04-24 |title=Allison Mack of \"Smallville\" granted bail in sex cult case |publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gonzalez |first=Sandra |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/04/24/entertainment/allison-mack/index.html |title=Allison Mack granted bail in sex trafficking case |work=CNN |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=May 3, 2018}}</ref> If convicted of all charges, Mack and Raniere face a minimum of fifteen years and up to [[life imprisonment|life in prison]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-smallville-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult-keith-raniere/ |title=\"Smallville\" actress Allison Mack arrested for role in NXIVM sex cult |last=Park |first=Andrea |date=April 21, 2018 |work=[[CBS News]]|access-date=May 16, 2018 |language=en}}</ref> On May 4, Raniere pleaded not guilty.<ref name=NBCMay4>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/self-help-guru-denies-enslaving-branding-women-sex-cult-n871441 |title=Self-help guru denies enslaving, branding women in sex cult |work=NBC News |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSalzman's home was raided shortly after Raniere's arrest,<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/> and prosecutors stated during his arraignment that further arrests and a superseding indictment for Raniere and Mack should be expected.<ref name=TimesUnion20180504>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Keith-Raniere-Allison-Mack-head-to-court-in-12887478.php |title=Raniere, Mack appear in court on sex-slavery charges |work=Albany Times-Union |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref name=News10May4>{{cite web |url=http://www.news10.com/news/local-news/trial-date-set-for-keith-raniere-and-allison-mack/1159493630 |title=Trial date set for Keith Raniere and Allison Mack |work=Albany News 10 |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref> In late May, authorities moved to seize two NXIVM-owned properties near Albany.<ref>{{cite web |title=Foreclosure Complaint Reveals NXIVM Sex Cult Rituals In Upstate New York |date=May 24, 2018|access-date=May 29, 2018 |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2018/05/24/nxivm-sex-cult-foreclose-halfmoon}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, the ''[[New York Post]]'' reported that NXIVM had moved to [[Brooklyn, New York]] and was being led by Clare Bronfman.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2018/04/21/sex-cult-moves-to-brooklyn-and-is-ready-for-war/ |title='Sex cult' moves to Brooklyn \u2014 and is ready for 'war' |first=Laura |last=Italiano |date=April 21, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> On June 12, 2018, the ''Times Union'' reported that NXIVM had suspended its operations due to \"extraordinary circumstances facing the company\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-suspends-all-operations-12987928.php |title=NXIVM suspends all operations; founder's bail denied |first1=Steve |last1=Hughes |first2=The Associated |last2=Press |date=June 12, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Bronfman was arrested on July 24 and charged with [[racketeering]]. She was released to house arrest after signing a $100 million [[bail bond]]. Also arrested and charged with the same crime were NXIVM President Nancy Salzman; her daughter, Lauren Salzman; and another NXIVM employee, Kathy Russell.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4350140/clare-bronfman-seagrams-arrested-nxivm-sex-cult/ |title=Clare Bronfman, Seagram's heiress, arrested in Nxivm sex-trafficking case |website=globalnews.ca |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/nxivm-bronfman-sex-cult-racketeering-1.4759640 |title=Seagram's heiress Clare Bronfman charged in connection with alleged sex cult NXIVM Bronfman and five others accused of racketeering related to operations of a cult-like pyramid group |last=Proctor |first=Jason |date=July 24, 2018 |website=CBC |access-date=July 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, 2019, Nancy Salzman pleaded guilty to a charge of racketeering criminal conspiracy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-crime-cult-idUSKCN1QU2Z2 |title=Self-help guru Raniere faces U.S. child porn charges; associate pleads guilty |last=Brendan |first=Pierson |date=March 13, 2019 |work=[[Reuters]]|access-date=March 14, 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2019/03/13/nxivm-co-founder-nancy-salzman-pleads-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Nxivm co-founder Nancy Salzman pleads guilty in sex cult case |last=Saul |first=Emily |date=March 13, 2019 |website=[[New York Post]] |language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=March 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/allison-mack-nxivm-case-smallville-actress-possible-plea-negotiations-keith-raniere-pleads-not-guilty-in-sex-cult-case/ |title=Leader of alleged NXIVM sex cult pleads not guilty to child porn charges |website=www.cbsnews.com |accessdate=April 9, 2019}}</ref> Also in March 2019, Lauren Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering and racketeering conspiracy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Daughter-of-NXIVM-leader-pleads-guilty-13725939.php |title=Daughter of NXIVM leader pleads guilty |first1=Brendan J. |last1=Lyons |first2=Mike |last2=Goodwin |date=March 29, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> On April 8, 2019, Mack pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/apr/08/allison-mack-nxivm-pleads-guilty-racketeering-charges |title=Smallville star Allison Mack pleads guilty to racketeering in Nxivm case |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=April 8, 2019 |accessdate=April 21, 2019}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to charges of [[Illegal immigration to the United States|harboring an alien]] and [[identity fraud]]; bookkeeper Russell also pleaded guilty to [[visa fraud]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/nyregion/nxivm-clare-bronfman.html |title=Clare Bronfman Pleads Guilty in Nxivm 'Sex Cult' Case, Leaving Leader to Stand Trial Alone |last=Meier |first=Barry |date=April 19, 2019 |work=The New York Times |access-date=April 20, 2019 |last2=Moynihan |first2=Colin |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nRaniere's federal trial began on May 7, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706/|title=Video Center|website=NEWS10 ABC}}</ref> On June 19, 2019, he was convicted of racketeering and sex trafficking.<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n\nIn January 2020, a federal lawsuit was filed in New York accusing Raniere and 14 associates of conducting illegal psychological experiments on members of the company and abusing them physically, emotionally and financially.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/29/us/nxivm-lawsuit-experiments-abuse/index.html|title=Nxivm leadership accused of illegal psychological experiments and systematic abuse in federal lawsuit|author1=Giulia McDonnell Nieto del Rio |author2=Madeline Holcombe |author3=Rob Frehse|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-21}}</ref>\n\n==Beliefs and practices==\n[[File:US v. Raniere GovtExhibit GX46.JPG|right|upright=0.7|thumb|NXIVM founder Keith Raniere]]\nIn NXIVM classes, rank was signified by the wearing of colored sashes, similar to belts used in various martial arts.<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/the-stripe-path-how-to-make-your-way-up-in-nxivm-1.4674369</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a 12-point \"Mission Statement\", which participants recited, pledging to \"purge\" themselves \"of all parasite and envy-based habits\", to enroll others in such courses, and to \"ethically control as much of the money, wealth and resources of the world as possible within my success plan\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/09/nyregion/nxivm-cult-trial.html |title=Former Sex Cult Official Describes Its 'Evil' Inner Workings |first=Colin |last=Moynihan |date=May 9, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Photographs of Raniere and Mack were displayed during classes, which would conclude with participants showing gratitude to the two leaders.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/escaping-nxivm |title=Uncover: Escaping NXIVM |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM conducted \"Intensives\" classes for 12 hours daily for 16 days. One cited price was $7,500.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/nxivm-trial-founder-keith-raniere-was-crime-boss-posing-as-guru-feds-say |title=NXIVM Trial Opens: Feds Say Founder Keith Raniere Was 'Crime Boss,' Not Guru |first=Pilar |last=Melendez |date=May 7, 2019 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref> Classes were divided into modules. In one module, \"Relationship Sourcing\", students were instructed to explore the benefits they would receive in the event of a partner's sudden death. Another module, \"Dracula and his ghouls\", reportedly discussed psychopaths and their followers. Other module titles included \"Best People; Perfect World\" and \"The Heroic Struggle\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/06/15/part-1-master-ranieres-secret-teachings-what-students-learn-in-esp-intensives/ |title=Part 1: Master Raniere's secret teachings: What students learn in ESP 'Intensives'! |date=June 15, 2017 |website=Frank Report - Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM featured a practice, termed \"exploration of meaning\" that involved senior members questioning members as they delved into their childhood memories.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/nxivm-8-things-we-learned-from-sex-cult-expose-630616/ |title=Nxivm: 8 Things We Learned from 'Sex-Cult' Expos\u00e9 |first1=Elisabeth |last1=Garber-Paul |first2=Elisabeth |last2=Garber-Paul |date=May 30, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM taught that some people, called \"Suppressives\", try to impede progress within NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Witness-After-leaving-NXIVM-women-became-targets-13841142.php |title=Witness: Raniere bragged of wanting to 'break' follower Allison Mack |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=May 13, 2019 |website=Times Union |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> People who irrevocably turned against Raniere were said to have undergone \"The Fall\" and were labeled, in the words of a former member, as \"Luciferians, lost people for whom bad feels good, and good feels bad.\"<ref name=\"auto5\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/06/keith-raniere-nxivm-patents-luciferian |title=How NXIVM Used a Simple Tool to Build Its \"Sex Cult\" |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM members organized \"Vanguard Week\", an annual celebration of Raniere's birthday.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-turned-Lake-George-resort-into-annual-13836853.php |title=NXIVM turned Lake George resort into annual Raniere birthday jamboree - SFChronicle.com |date=May 10, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNXIVM has been associated with several related organizations. '''Jness''' was a society aimed at women, while the '''Society of Protectors''' was aimed primarily at men.<ref name=\"rollingstone.com\"/> A third group was known by the acronym DOS for \"'''Dominus Obsequious Sororium'''\", a Latin phrase that reportedly translates to \"Master over Slave Women\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/feds-self-help-guru-kept-women-as-sex-slaves-branded-them-with-his-initials |title=Feds: 'Self-Help' Guru Kept Women as Sex 'Slaves,' Branded Them With His Initials |first=Tatyana |last=Bellamy-Walker |date=March 27, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref>  In 2006, Raniere founded '''Rainbow Cultural Garden''', an international chain of child-care organizations in which children were to be exposed to seven different languages.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/alejandro-sanzs-wifes-miami-school-closed-by-state-tied-to-nxivm-sex-cult-founder-10295903 |title=State Closes Midtown Miami School Tied to NXIVM \"Sex Cult\" Leader |first=Jerry |last=Iannelli |date=April 27, 2018 |website=Miami New Times}}</ref>\n\nSome members of NXIVM's inner circle were reportedly taught that, in past lives, they were high-ranking [[Nazi]]s.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Suzanna |last=Andrews |website=Vanities |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> Barbara Bouchey was reportedly the reincarnation of Holocaust architect [[Reinhard Heydrich]], while Nancy Salzmann was supposed to be the reincarnation of Hitler. Raniere reported he had been a leader of anti-Nazi partisans.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2018/04/08/adolf-hitler-herman-goering-nxivm-sex-cult-leader-raniere-told-followers-reincarnated-nazis/ |title=From Adolf Hitler to Herman Goering, NXIVM sex-cult leader Raniere told followers they were 'Reincarnated Nazis'! |date=April 9, 2018 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a complaint filed by a former NXIVM member, a medical doctor performed an experiment on her that involved recording her EEG responses while viewing footage of people being murdered.<ref name=\"auto5\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://assets.documentcloud.org/documents/4113542/Porter-Complaint.pdf|title=Porter Complaint}}</ref> Brandon P. Porter, the doctor, faced 24 professional conduct charges from the New York State Board of the [[Office of Professional Medical Conduct]], including \"moral unfitness to practice medicine\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/article/NXIVM-doctor-facing-state-charges-12890993.php |title=NXIVM doctor facing state charges |first=Steve |last=Barnes |date=May 5, 2018 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://apps.health.ny.gov/pubdoh/professionals/doctors/conduct/factions/FileDownloadAction.action?finalActionId=12236&fileName=CHRG+253486.pdf&fileSeqNum=1 |title=Notice Of Hearing In The Matter Of Brandon Porter, MD |publisher=Office for Professional Medical Conduct, New York State Department of Health |date=April 24, 2018 |accessdate=July 22, 2019}}</ref>  In August 2019, Porter's license was revoked for his role in the experiments and for his failure to report an \"unusual disease outbreak\" which occurred at NXIVM's 2016 \"V-Week\" retreat.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/NXIVM-doctor-who-conducted-brain-studies-loses-14370824.php |title=NXIVM doctor who conducted brain studies loses license |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/08/22/dr-brandon-porter-loses-medical-license/ |title=Dr. Brandon Porter Loses Medical License |date=August 22, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n==Notable members and others==\nNXIVM was founded by '''Keith Raniere''' (born August 26, 1960).<ref name=\"RollingStone20180328\"/> In March 2018, Raniere was arrested and [[indictment|indicted]] on a variety of charges related to [[NXIVM#Media investigations|DOS]] (a \"secret sisterhood\" within NXIVM), including [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]], and conspiracy to commit [[forced labor]].<ref name=\"NBCNY20180326\"/><ref name=\"NBCNews0516\"/><ref name=\"news10.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.news10.com/video/nxivm-trial-prosecution-s-opening-statements-lasted-90-minutes_20190507163116/1986277706 |title=NXIVM TRIAL: Prosecution's opening statements lasted 90 minutes |date=May 7, 2019 |website=WTEN}}</ref> He was found guilty of all charges at trial.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chow |first1=Andrew |title=NXIVM Leader Keith Raniere Convicted on Sex Trafficking Charges. Here Are the Major Players in the Case |url=https://time.com/5568135/nxivm-allison-mack-raniere/ |website=Time |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=June 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, Keith Raniere met '''Nancy Salzman''', a psychiatric nurse and trained practitioner of [[Hypnosis|hypnotism]] and [[Neuro-Linguistic Programming]]. The two founded \"Executive Success Programs\", a personal development company<ref name=\"auto2\"/> offering a range of techniques aimed at [[self-improvement]].<ref name=\"Newsweek20180328\"/><ref name=\"AECEB\"/><ref name=\"NYT20180530\"/>  In March 2019, Salzman pleaded guilty to racketeering.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/who-nancy-salzman-nxivm-co-founders-wrongdoings-shine-through-daughter-lauren-1431652 |title=Who is Nancy Salzman? Co-founder's daughter testifies in plea deal for NXIVM wrongdoings |first=Kelly Wynne On 5/21/19 at 11:22 AM |last=EDT |date=May 21, 2019 |website=Newsweek}}</ref> \n\n[[File:Bronfman sara.jpg|thumb|left|100px|Heiress Sara Bronfman, along with her sister Clare, bankrolled the NXIVM organization beginning in 2003.]]\n\n'''[[Sara Bronfman]]''' is the daughter of billionaire Seagrams chairman Edgar Bronfman Sr.  She was introduced to NXIVM by a family friend in 2002.<ref name=\"auto3\"/> She in turn introduced her sister, '''[[Clare Bronfman]]''' to NXIVM. Clare Bronfman was arrested by federal agents on July 24, 2018, in New York City and charged with money laundering and identity theft in connection with NXIVM activities. She pleaded not guilty in the [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of New York]] in Brooklyn. She was released on $100 million bond and placed on [[house arrest]] with [[electronic monitoring]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/crime-courts/feds-arrest-seagram-heiress-bronfman-nxivm-sex-slave-case-n894136 |title=Seagram heiress Bronfman pleads not guilty in NXIVM 'sex slave' case |work=NBC News| access-date=April 20, 2019 |date=July 24, 2018}}</ref> On April 19, 2019, Bronfman pleaded guilty to conspiracy to conceal and harbor illegal aliens for financial gain and fraudulent use of identification. She faces 21 to 27 months in prison and has agreed to forfeit $6 million.<ref name=lyons>{{cite news |title=Bronfman, Russell plead guilty in NXIVM case |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Bronfman-Russell-to-plead-guilty-in-NXIVM-case-13780718.php |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=April 20, 2019 |newspaper=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Emiliano Salinas]]''' is a venture capitalist and businessman. He is the son of former Mexican president [[Carlos Salinas de Gortari]].  Salinas served as vice president of Prorsus Capital, a financial consortium with ties to Raniere and NXIVM.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zimmerman |first1=Amy |title=Inside the NXIVM Sex Cult\u2019s Secret Plot to Take Over Mexico |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/inside-the-nxivm-sex-cults-secret-plot-to-take-over-mexico |website=The Daily Beast |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n[[File:Allison Mack at ComicCon 2009 NN.jpg|thumb|right|150px|American actress [[Allison Mack]] pleaded guilty to racketeering charges in April 2019 and is awaiting sentencing.]]\n\n'''Karen A. Unterreiner''' is a member who became Raniere's live-in partner beginning in the 1980s, and an early employee of his company Consumers' Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://newsinteractives.cbc.ca/longform/the-making-of-the-vanguard |title=Escaping NXIVM: Inside the secretive world of leader Keith Raniere |first1=Josh |last1=Bloch |first2=Kathleen |last2=Goldhar |first3=Anita |last3=Elash |first4=Dave |last4=Pizer |website=newsinteractives.cbc.ca}}</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Raniere-stands-alone-13795442.php |title=Raniere stands alone |date=May 4, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref> \n\n'''Pam Cafritz''' was the daughter of Washington-DC socialites Buffy and William Cafritz.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2010/11/bronfman-201011 |title=The Heiresses and the Cult |first=Cond\u00e9 |last=Nast |website=Vanity Fair}}</ref>  In the 1990s, she resided with Raniere and Karen Unterreiner in an Albany home.  Both Unterreiner and Cafritz signed consent agreements with prosecutors for their role in Consumer's Buyline.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/07/making-vanguard-proud-the-mays-men-bring-executive-success-to-arkansas/ |title=Making Vanguard Proud \u2013 The Mays Men Bring Executive Success To Arkansas |date=July 7, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref> Cafritz was a founder of JNESS, the Raniere-affiliated women's group.  Cafritz was reported to be Raniere's 'most important long-term girlfriend'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/30/magazine/sex-cult-empowerment-nxivm-keith-raniere.html |title=Inside Nxivm, the 'Sex Cult' That Preached Empowerment |first=Vanessa |last=Grigoriadis |date=May 30, 2018 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>  On November 7, 2016, Pam Cafritz died.  After her death, her credit card was charged for over $300,000.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Ordered-to-seduce-Raniere-woman-planned-escape-13968629.php |title=Ordered to seduce Raniere, woman planned escape from NXIVM |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Times Union}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Allison Mack]]''' is an American actress known for her role on the series ''[[Smallville]]''. Mack was reportedly recruited to the [[Vancouver]] chapter of NXIVM, along with her ''Smallville'' co-star [[Kristin Kreuk]].<ref>{{cite news |title=How to Lose $100 Million |first=Nicholas |last=K\u00f6hler |url=http://www2.macleans.ca/2010/09/09/how-to-lose-100-million/ |newspaper=[[Maclean's]] |date=September 13, 2010 |accessdate=November 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180502001435/http://www.macleans.ca/economy/business/how-to-lose-100-million/2/ |archive-date=May 2, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>  Mack was reportedly a founder of DOS, a Raniere-affiliated Master/Slave group. Mack was arrested on April 20, 2018, on charges of [[sex trafficking]], sex trafficking [[conspiracy (criminal)|conspiracy]], and [[forced labor]] conspiracy.  Mack pleaded guilty to [[racketeering]] charges in April 2019, and was to be sentenced in September 2019. However, on July 15, 2019 the Senior U.S. District Judge Nicholas Garaufis postponed the sentencing until further notice to allow federal probation officials to conduct pre-sentencing investigations.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sentencing of NXIVM leader delayed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/amp/Sentencing-of-NXIVM-leader-delayed-14097454.php |newspaper=[[timesunion]]}}</ref>\n\n[[File:10.15.11NickiClyneByLuigiNovi2.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Canadian actress [[Nicki Clyne]]]]\n'''[[Nicki Clyne]]''' is a Canadian actress known for her role on the series ''[[Battlestar Galactica (2004 TV series)|Battlestar Galactica]]''.  According to reports, in 2006, Clyne became involved with NXIVM. In 2008, she reportedly requested to be let out of her contract to focus full-time on NXIVM.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2017/11/19/nicki-clyne-quit-acting-broke-her-contract-with-battlestar-galatica-producers-to-join-nxivm-mission-full-time/ |title=Nicki Clyne quit acting, broke her contract with Battlestar Galatica producers to join NXIVM mission full time |date=November 19, 2017 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n\n'''India Oxenberg''', daughter of actress [[Catherine Oxenberg]], was introduced to the group in 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/catherine-oxenberg-on-losing-her-daughter-to-the-sex-cult-nxivm-going-public-was-a-last-resort |title=Catherine Oxenberg Reveals How She Lost Her Daughter to the Sex Cult NXIVM |first=Amy |last=Zimmerman |date=August 8, 2018 |publisher= |accessdate=June 20, 2019 |via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref> At Raniere's trial, a witness testified that India had spent a year on a 500-calorie-per-day diet.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/allison-mack-nxivm-trial-diet-500-calories-1443377 |title=Allison Mack reportedly forced NXIVM sex cult members to follow 500-calorie-a-day diets |first=Janice Williams On 6/11/19 at 10:42 AM |last=EDT |date=June 11, 2019 |website=Newsweek |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> In May 2017, India admitted to her mother that she was among those who had been branded.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-daughter-being-branded-nxivm/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg's Daughter Was 'Branded' with 'Cult' Leader's Initials: 'I Was Horrified' |website=PEOPLE.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref> India left the group in June 2018, after Raniere's arrest.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://people.com/crime/catherine-oxenberg-says-her-daughter-who-has-left-nxivm-is-moving-forward/ |title=Catherine Oxenberg Says Her Daughter Who Has Left Nxivm Is 'Moving Forward' |first1=Liz |last1=McNeil |first2=Johnny |last2=Dodd |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=August 7, 2018 |access-date=February 7, 2019}}</ref> In August 2018, Catherine Oxenberg's book ''Captive: A Mother's Crusade to Save Her Daughter from a Terrifying Cult'' was published.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.simonandschuster.com/books/Captive/Catherine-Oxenberg/9781982100650 |title=Captive |last1=Oxenberg |first1=Catherine |first2=Natasha |last2=Stoynoff |date=2018 |publisher=[[Gallery Publishing Group|Gallery Books]] |isbn=9781982100650}}</ref>\n\n===Critical former members===\n'''Toni Natalie''' met Raniere in 1991 when he was pitching his business \"Consumer's Buyline\".<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.democratandchronicle.com/story/news/politics/albany/2018/03/08/rochester-woman-battles-nxivm-keith-raniere/360847002/ |title=Rochester woman tells all about life with NXIVM's Keith Raniere, her ex |website=Rochester Democrat and Chronicle}}</ref> Natalie and her then-husband became top sellers for the organization.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>  Natalie recalled that she was able to stop smoking after a two-hour session with Raniere,<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> but this claim is disputed by her ex-husband.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/10/17/toni-natalies-keith-hypnotized-me-into-quitting-smoking-story-disputed-by-ex-husband-rusty/ |title=Toni Natalie's 'Keith Hypnotized Me Into Quitting Smoking' Story Disputed by Ex-Husband Rusty |last=Parlato |first=Frank |website=Frank Report |date=October 17, 2019}}</ref> Natalie and her son later moved to be near Raniere; her marriage ended shortly thereafter. Natalie and Raniere dated for the next eight years.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In the mid-90s, Raniere and Natalie operated a health-products store.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web |url=http://forbes/2003/1013/088 |title=Cult of Personality |first=Michael |last=Freedman |website=Forbes}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 1999, Raniere's eight-year relationship with Natalie ended. Natalie would subsequently claim to have been the victim of harassment.<ref>[https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084744]{{dead link|date=June 2019}}</ref> In a January 2003 ruling, federal judge Robert Littlefield implied Raniere was using a legal suit to harass Natalie. Wrote Littlefield: \"This matter smacks of a jilted fellow's attempt at revenge or retaliation against his former girlfriend, with many attempts at tripping her up along the way\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.org/details/269747-natalie-jilted-boyfriend |title=Natalie Jilted Boyfriend |date=December 1, 2011 |publisher= |via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/> In 2011, Natalie filed documents in federal court alleging that she had been repeatedly raped by Raniere.<ref name=\"democratandchronicle.com\"/>\n\n'''Joseph J. O'Hara''' was an attorney who departed NXIVM in 2005 after accusing the group of misdeeds.   In 2007, O'Hara was indicted by Albany County.  It was later revealed that the District Attorney had allowed Raniere's girlfriend Kristin Keeffe to operate within its office as a sort of victims' advocate.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-pressed-district-attorney-3379748.php |title=NXIVM pressed district attorney |date=March 3, 2012}}</ref> Charges were ultimately dismissed.\n\n'''Barbara Bouchey''' was a client of Nancy Salzman, having been referred to her in 1988. Beginning in 2000, Bouchey dated Raniere. In 2009, Bouchey and eight other women (\"The NXIVM Nine\") confronted Raniere with concerns about abuse within the organization. That year, Bouchey left the group and later went to law enforcement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/news/article/Guilty-plea-of-Salzman-ends-her-long-allegiance-13691433.php |title=Guilty plea ends Salzman's long allegiance to Raniere - TimesUnion.com |date=March 17, 2019 |website=www.timesunion.com |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Kristin Keeffe''' became Raniere's partner in the early 1990s.  In 2013, Keeffe gave birth to Raniere's son Gaelyn.<ref name=\"TU150920\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/tuplus-local/article/Legal-papers-NXIVM-officials-probed-finances-of-6516856.php |title=Legal papers: NXIVM officials probed finances of 6 federal judges, Senator Schumer, others |first=Brendan J. |last=Lyons |date=September 20, 2015 |website=Times Union}}</ref>  In February 2014, Keeffe broke with Raniere and his group. Fleeing the region with her son, an email bearing Keeffe's name explained: \"I have full sole legal custody of Gaelyn. Keith was experimenting on him. I had to get Gaelyn away\".<ref name=\"TU140511\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/A-split-from-NXIVM-5468731.php |title=A split from NXIVM |first=James M. |last=Odato |date=May 11, 2014 |website=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]]}}</ref> Keeffe publicly described Raniere as \"dangerous\".<ref name=\"TU140511\"/>  In 2015, Keeffe alleged that NXIVM leaders had planned to lure critics to Mexico with an invitation to an anti-cult conference; once in Mexico, the critics were to be arrested on false charges by order of a judge who had been bribed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://culteducation.com/404-error-page.html |title=404 Error Page |website=culteducation.com|access-date=August 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811212201/https://www.culteducation.com/404-error-page.html|archive-date=August 11, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"cbc.ca\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/transcripts/transcript-uncover-escaping-nxivm-season-1-ep-3-1.5084740 |title=TRANSCRIPT: Uncover: Escaping NXIVM - Season 1, EP 3 |work=[[CBC Radio]] |date=April 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"TU151018\">{{cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Records-NXIVM-hacked-billionaire-s-emails-with-6576310.php |title=Records: NXIVM hacked billionaire's emails with Hillary Clinton, world leaders |work=[[Times Union (Albany)|Times Union]] |last=Lyons |first=Brendan J. |date=October 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Sarah Edmondson]]''' is a Canadian actress. After leaving NXIVM in early 2017, she publicly denounced the organization, claiming that she was invited into \"DOS,\" a substructure within NXIVM operated by Keith Raniere and [[Allison Mack]], and was branded with Raniere's and Mack's initials at Mack's Albany home.<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite web |title=Inside a Secretive Group Where Women Are Branded |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/17/nyregion/nxivm-women-branded-albany.html |accessdate=May 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |title=Former NXIVM member says she was invited into a secret sorority, then branded |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/nxivm-member-invited-secret-sorority-branded/story?id=51617201 |accessdate=May 13, 2018 |agency=ABC News |date=December 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nxivm member was branded at Allison Mack's home |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/nxivm-member-was-branded-at-allison-macks-home-video-1113006 |accessdate=May 18, 2018 |agency=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> Edmondson showed the brand in a ''[[New York Times]]'' expos\u00e9 of NXIVM.<ref name=\"nyt\"/>\n\n'''Mark Vicente''', a filmmaker known for the 2004 film ''[[What the Bleep Do We Know!?]]'', began involvement with the group in 2005. Vicente testified against Raniere at his 2019 trial.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tonyortega.org/2019/05/09/filmmaker-breaks-down-describing-nxivms-duplicitous-ideas-and-evil-intent/ |title=Filmmaker breaks down describing Nxivm's duplicitous ideas and evil intent - The Underground Bunker |website=tonyortega.org |accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Journalists and bloggers===\n'''James Odato''' is an investigative reporter who wrote for the Albany Times Union.  In 2012, Odato reported Raniere's history of pedophilia.   In October 2013, Odato was named in a lawsuit filed by NXIVM, along with Vanity Fair's Suzanna Andrews and blogger John J. Tighe;  all had written critically of the group.<ref name=\"politico.com\">{{Cite web |url=http://politi.co/1W2nbYE |title=Journalist on leave after tangle with secretive 'NXIVM' group |first=Joe |last=Pompeo |website=POLITICO Media}}</ref>  The suit alleged that NXIVM computers had been illegally accessed.   Shortly thereafter, Odato was described as being 'on leave' from the Times Union.<ref name=\"politico.com\"/>\n\nIn 2007, '''Frank Parlato''' was hired by NXIVM to help with publicity.  After concluding the members were being defrauded by Raniere, Parlato began blogging about the group on his sites \"ArtVoice\", \"The Niagara Falls Reporter\" and \"The Frank Report\".<ref>Vice News Tonight May 16, 2018\"</ref><ref name=\"timesunion.com\"/>\n\n'''John Tighe''' wrote about NXIVM on a blog.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/Secret-mission-A-child-589818.php |title=Secret mission: A child |first=JAMES M. ODATO Capitol |last=bureau |date=July 25, 2010 |website=Times Union}}</ref> In 2013, NXIVM accused Tighe of illegally accessing NXIVM servers using a former member's login information. Tighe's home was raided by the New York State Police, and his computer was seized.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.timesunion.com/local/article/NXIVM-hacking-case-to-be-tossed-6827893.php |title=NXIVM hacking case to be tossed |first=Robert |last=Gavin |date=February 13, 2016 |website=Times Union}}</ref> Several months later, State Police announced the discovery of child pornography on Tighe's computer; he was arrested. Facing a possible prison term of 20 years, Tighe pleaded guilty to a single count in exchange for a five-year sentence in federal prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/06/25/is-john-tighe-innocent-heres-a-few-facts-to-consider/ |title=Is John Tighe Innocent? \u2013 Here're a Few Facts to Consider |first=Is John Tighe Innocent?-Here\u2019re a Few Facts to Consider |last=says |date=June 25, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref>\n\n==Films, documentaries and books==\n* [[Investigation Discovery]] will release a two-hour special ''The Lost Women of NXIVM''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/investigation-discovery-the-lost-women-of-nxivm-1202635465/ |title='The Lost Women Of Nxivm': Investigation Discovery Explores Sex Cult In Two-Hour Special |first1=Peter |last1=White |first2=Peter |last2=White |date=June 20, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[HBO]] has announced their plans of making a docuseries about NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/04/nxivm-documentary-series-hbo-jehane-noujaim-karim-amer-1202060308/ |title=NXIVM Documentary Series from 'The Square' Filmmakers Coming to HBO |first1=Steve |last1=Greene |first2=Steve |last2=Greene |date=April 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/hbo-plans-docuseries-alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-1203073 |title=HBO Plans Docuseries on Alleged Sex Cult NXIVM |website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/tv/alleged-sex-cult-nxivm-focus-hbo-documentary-series-n996196 |title=Alleged sex cult NXIVM focus of HBO documentary series |website=NBC News}}</ref>\n* [[Catherine Oxenberg]] produced a film for [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] about her daughter's experiences with NXIVM<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/tv/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime/ |title=Lifetime Is Making a NXIVM Sex Cult Movie After Founder Keith Raniere's Conviction |website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/nxivm-sex-cult-movie-lifetime-catherine-oxenberg-peter-facinelli-star-1202637998/ |title=NXIVM Sex Cult Movie Set At Lifetime With Catherine Oxenberg Producing; Peter Facinelli & Andrea Roth To Star |first1=Denise |last1=Petski |first2=Denise |last2=Petski |date=July 1, 2019}}</ref> It is titled ''[[Escaping the NXIVM Cult: A Mother's Fight to Save Her Daughter]]'' and aired on September 21, 2019. While Catherine Oxenberg served as the narrator and executive producer, the film starred [[Andrea Roth]] as Catherine Oxenberg, [[Peter Facinelli]] as Keith Raniere, and [[Sara Fletcher]] as Allison Mack.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lifetime's Trailer For 'Escaping The NXIVM Cult' Shows Seduction And Anguish |url=https://deadline.com/video/lifetimes-trailer-for-escaping-the-nxivm-cult-shows-seduction-and-anguish/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n* \"The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM\" is an upcoming book by Toni Natalie and Chet Hardin set for release on September 24, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://artvoice.com/2019/07/28/new-book-by-toni-natalie-the-program-inside-the-mind-of-keith-raniere-and-the-rise-and-fall-of-nxivm/ |title=New Book by Toni Natalie: 'The Program: Inside the Mind of Keith Raniere and the Rise and Fall of NXIVM' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Artvoice}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=https://www.grandcentralpublishing.com/titles/toni-natalie/the-program/9781538701034/ |title=The Program |date=March 5, 2019 |via=www.grandcentralpublishing.com}}</ref>\n* ''Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life'' by [[Sarah Edmondson]] is a book set that was released on September 17, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://frankreport.com/2019/07/28/scarred-the-true-story-of-how-i-escaped-nxivm-the-cult-that-bound-my-life/ |title=New Book By Sarah Edmondson 'Scarred: The True Story of How I Escaped NXIVM, the Cult That Bound My Life' |date=July 28, 2019 |website=Frank Report &#124; Investigative Journalism From Frank Parlato}}</ref>\n* NXIVM was the subject on an episode ''[[E! True Hollywood Story]]'' which featured interviews from several journalists and the people that were once involved with the organization including Catherine Oxenberg, Sarah Edmondson, and actor and Oxenberg's real-life friend [[Callum Blue]].1\n*[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] released a podcast in 2018 on NXIVM as part of CBC [https://www.cbc.ca/radio/uncover/uncover-season-1-escaping-nxivm-1.4675949 Uncover Season 1].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180421090811/http://www.keithraniere.com/ Website] of [[Keith Raniere]]\n* [http://www.scs.cmu.edu/~dst/NXIVM/ Three critical articles pertaining to the ''NXIVM v. Ross Institute'' lawsuit]\n* [http://www.timesunion.com/nxivm/ ''Times Union'' Special Report on NXIVM]\n\n{{Multi-level marketing}}\n\n[[Category:1998 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Albany County, New York]]\n[[Category:Colonie, New York]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1998]]\n[[Category:Large-group awareness training]]\n[[Category:Multi-level marketing companies]]\n[[Category:Privately held companies based in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Sexual misconduct allegations]]\n[[Category:Cults]]\n", "name_user": "CplDHicks2", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCritical former members:added contradictory template; the referenced Hollywood Reporter article says it was Mack's home, but the New York Times expos\u00e9 says it was Lauren Salzman's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NXIVM"}
{"title_page": "Elodie Keene", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name                      = Elodie Keene\n| image                     = \n| image_size                = \n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_name                = \n| othername                 =\n| birth_date                = {{birth date and age|1949|04|10}}\n| birth_place               = [[Berkeley, California]], U.S.\n| death_date                = \n| death_place               = \n| alma_mater                = \n| occupation                = Film director, television director, television editor, television producer\n| years_active              = 1979\u2013present\n| spouse                    = [[imdbname:0287416|Bruce Fortune]]<br>(?\u2013present; 2 children)\n| parents                   = Yvonne Cyr Keene Koshland <br> Jim Keene\n| family                    = [[Christopher Keene]] (brother)<br>[[Daniel E. Koshland Jr.]] (stepfather)\n}}\n\n'''Elodie Keene''' (born April 10, 1949 in [[Berkeley, California|Berkeley]], [[California]]) is an American film/television director, producer and editor. As a television director her credits include ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'', ''[[NYPD Blue]]'', ''[[The Practice]]'', ''[[Ally McBeal]]'', ''[[Charmed]]'', ''[[Felicity (TV series)|Felicity]]'', ''[[The Wire]]'', ''[[House (TV series)|House, M.D.]]'', ''[[The Closer]]'', ''[[Nip/Tuck]]'' and among other series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/84/Elodie-Keene.html |title=Elodie Keene Biography (1948-) |publisher=Film Reference |accessdate=September 27, 2011}}</ref>\n\nShe has won three [[Primetime Emmy Awards]], two for best dramatic series and one for best editing in a single camera series, all for her work on ''[[L.A. Law]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emmys.com/award_history_search?person=+Elodie+Keene&program=&start_year=1949&end_year=2010&network=All&web_category=All&winner=All |title=Elodie Keene Primetime Emmy Award wins and nominations |publisher=Primetime Emmy\u00ae Award Database |accessdate=September 27, 2011}}</ref> Elodie Keene is the daughter of Yvonne (n\u00e9e Cyr) and Jim Keene.<ref>{{Cite web|first= |last= |authorlink= |title= Daniel Koshland, Jr. Retrospective Oral History Project: Yvonne Koshland - Interviews conducted by Sally Smith Hughes in 2011|publisher=[[University of California - Berkeley]] Regional Oral History Office - The Bancroft Library |date= 2014|url=http://digitalassets.lib.berkeley.edu/roho/ucb/text/koshland_yvonne_2014.pdf  |accessdate=}}</ref> Her mother was of [[Acadians|Acadian]], [[German Americans|German]], and [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]] descent.<ref>Smith, p. 1</ref> Her parents divorced in 1953 and her mother remarried to Jim San Jule in 1954 until their divorce in 1970.<ref>Smith, p. 6</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Dave |last=Weinstein |authorlink=   |title=Jim San Jule: Tireless Crusader   |publisher=Eichler Network|date= |url=https://www.eichlernetwork.com/article/jim-san-jule-tireless-crusader?page=0,0  |accessdate=April 5, 2019}}</ref> She has three siblings: Philip Keene (born 1941), [[Christopher Keene]] (born 1946),<ref>Smith, p. 5</ref> and Tamsen (n\u00e9e San Jule) Calhoon (born 1956).<ref>Smith, p. 6</ref> Her mother remarried to biochemist [[Daniel E. Koshland Jr.]] in 2000, of the Haas family, the owners of [[Levi Strauss & Co]].\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Director===\n\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:90%:background:#f9f9f9 border=2 cellpadding=4\n|- align=center\n! style=background:#B0C4DE | Year\n! style=background:#B0C4DE | Film\n! style=background:#B0C4DE | Episode Title\n! style=background:#B0C4DE | Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1990\n|rowspan=18|''[[L.A. Law]]''\n|\"The Bitch Is Back\"\n|Season 5, episode 1\n|-\n|\"Forgive Me Father, for I Have Sued\"\n|Season 4, episode 20\n|-\n|rowspan=4|1991\n|\"TV or Not TV\"\n|Season 6, episode 2\n|-\n|\"There Goes the Judge\"\n|Season 5, episode 20\n|-\n|\"He's a Crowd\"\n|Season 5, episode 12\n|-\n|\"Splatoon\"\n|Seaso